WEBVTT

1
00:00:32.041 --> 00:00:35.166
["Chopin's Nocturne in C Sharp" playing]

2
00:01:36.624 --> 00:01:38.082
[bomb explodes in the distance]

3
00:01:43.416 --> 00:01:45.082
[bomb explodes nearby]

4
00:01:45.624 --> 00:01:47.582
[bomb explodes]
[glass shatters]

5
00:01:48.999 --> 00:01:49.957
[continues playing]

6
00:01:50.666 --> 00:01:51.832
[bomb explodes]

7
00:01:51.999 --> 00:01:53.999
[continues playing]

8
00:01:55.374 --> 00:01:56.541
[bomb explodes]

9
00:01:59.124 --> 00:02:00.541
[continues playing]

10
00:02:00.624 --> 00:02:01.791
[bomb explodes]

11
00:02:05.124 --> 00:02:06.166
[continues playing]

12
00:02:06.249 --> 00:02:07.207
[bomb explodes]

13
00:02:12.832 --> 00:02:14.832
[screaming]

14
00:02:15.082 --> 00:02:17.082
[indistinct shouting]

15
00:02:21.874 --> 00:02:23.707
-Mr. Szpilman?
-Hello.

16
00:02:23.957 --> 00:02:26.457
I came specially to meet you.
I love your playing.

17
00:02:26.541 --> 00:02:30.582
-Who are you?
-My name's Dorota, Jurek's sister.

18
00:02:30.666 --> 00:02:33.291
-You're bleeding!
-It's nothing.

19
00:02:33.374 --> 00:02:37.291
You can write him a fan letter later.
This isn't the best time. Come on.

20
00:02:37.457 --> 00:02:39.791
Jurek, where have you been hiding her?

21
00:02:44.041 --> 00:02:46.791
-[father] I don't know what to take.
-[mother] You always take too much.

22
00:02:48.374 --> 00:02:49.666
[Regina]
How many suitcases are you taking?

23
00:02:49.749 --> 00:02:50.832
[Halina] I'm packing my red dress.

24
00:02:50.916 --> 00:02:52.374
[father]
And what, what do you think, should I,

25
00:02:52.457 --> 00:02:53.957
Should I take uncle Szymon's portrait?

26
00:02:54.041 --> 00:02:55.082
[siren wails in background]

27
00:02:55.166 --> 00:02:57.082
Take it, don't take it,
take what you like.

28
00:02:57.916 --> 00:03:02.457
-Can't you see I'm worried sick?
-Oh... He’ll come home, he’ll be alright.

29
00:03:02.624 --> 00:03:03.791
[Halina] We should have
another case just for shoes.

30
00:03:03.874 --> 00:03:06.666
Wladek, oh! Mama, Wladek's home!

31
00:03:06.832 --> 00:03:11.082
Oh! Thank God. Wladek! You're wounded?

32
00:03:11.166 --> 00:03:12.832
No, no, no,
it's a little cut, it's nothing.

33
00:03:12.916 --> 00:03:14.582
Oh, I've been worried sick.

34
00:03:14.666 --> 00:03:17.249
I told her not to worry.
You had your papers on you.

35
00:03:17.332 --> 00:03:19.249
If you'd been hit by a bomb,
they'd have known where to take you.

36
00:03:19.416 --> 00:03:20.582
-[Halina laughs]
-Henryk, Henryk,

37
00:03:20.666 --> 00:03:22.707
don't say things like...
don't say things like that.

38
00:03:22.791 --> 00:03:24.624
-[father] I can't find anything.
-God forbid. God forbid.

39
00:03:24.707 --> 00:03:26.582
-Papa, Wladek's home.
-What did I tell you?

40
00:03:26.666 --> 00:03:27.624
-[Wladek] What are you doing?
-[Regina] What's it look like we're doing?

41
00:03:27.791 --> 00:03:29.624
[Halina] Has anybody seen
my hat with the wide brim?

42
00:03:30.791 --> 00:03:32.791
I don't know they bombed us,
we're off the air.

43
00:03:32.957 --> 00:03:34.624
Warsaw's not the only radio station.

44
00:03:34.707 --> 00:03:37.541
Ah? Pack, pack, darling.
Get your things, pack.

45
00:03:37.624 --> 00:03:39.999
-Where are we going?
-P*. Out of Warsaw.

46
00:03:40.082 --> 00:03:41.832
-Out of Warsaw where?
-[Regina] You haven't heard?

47
00:03:42.624 --> 00:03:44.207
-Heard what?
-Haven't you seen the paper?

48
00:03:44.291 --> 00:03:47.041
-Oh, where's the paper?
-I used it for packing.

49
00:03:47.124 --> 00:03:48.041
[sirens wail nearby]

50
00:03:48.207 --> 00:03:49.332
Oh, she used it for packing.

51
00:03:49.416 --> 00:03:50.541
[father]
The government's moved to Lublin.

52
00:03:50.624 --> 00:03:52.457
AII able bodied men must leave the city,

53
00:03:52.541 --> 00:03:55.374
go across the river and set up a new line
of defense, that's what it said.

54
00:03:55.541 --> 00:03:58.999
There's hardly anybody left in this
building only the women the men have gone.

55
00:03:59.082 --> 00:04:01.957
And what do you think you’ll do while
you're setting up a new line of defense?

56
00:04:02.041 --> 00:04:05.916
-Wonder around lugging your suitcases?
-[mother] Pack, Wladek. There's no time.

57
00:04:05.999 --> 00:04:09.916
-I'm not going anywhere.
-Good! I'm not going anywhere either!

58
00:04:09.999 --> 00:04:12.374
[mother] Don't be ridiculous,
we've got to keep together.

59
00:04:12.457 --> 00:04:13.457
No, no, look, look.

60
00:04:13.541 --> 00:04:16.332
If I'm going to die, I prefer to die
in my own home, staying put.

61
00:04:16.416 --> 00:04:19.332
-[mother] God forbid.
-Sssh! Shut up! I've got something listen.

62
00:04:19.416 --> 00:04:22.416
[radio announcer]
<i>...from the BBC in London.</i>

63
00:04:22.916 --> 00:04:29.832
<i>The British government... having received
no reply to the ultimatum presented...</i>

64
00:04:29.916 --> 00:04:31.541
<i>to the German government...</i>

65
00:04:31.791 --> 00:04:34.999
<i>has declared war on Nazi Germany.</i>

66
00:04:35.082 --> 00:04:38.999
-Oh, oh, that's wonderful! Wonderful!
-[radio announcer] <i>It is expected that...</i>

67
00:04:39.082 --> 00:04:43.791
[radio static cross wires
with German radio announcer]

68
00:04:44.541 --> 00:04:46.582
[radio announcer]
<i>... within the next few hours,</i>

69
00:04:46.666 --> 00:04:49.582
<i>France will make a similar declaration.</i>

70
00:04:49.874 --> 00:04:52.332
<i>Poland is no longer alone.</i>

71
00:04:52.416 --> 00:04:53.541
-[mother] My God!
-[father] Oh! Oh!

72
00:04:53.624 --> 00:04:57.457
[Polish national anthem plays]

73
00:04:57.541 --> 00:05:00.791
[father] It's great, great,
wonderful, wonderful!

74
00:05:02.332 --> 00:05:06.124
-Mama, that was a great dinner.
-[Wladek] Hm! Yes, it certainly was.

75
00:05:06.499 --> 00:05:09.166
Well, when there's something to celebrate,
you've got to make an effort.

76
00:05:09.249 --> 00:05:11.541
Here's to Great Britain and France!

77
00:05:12.749 --> 00:05:16.166
[father] I told you. Didn't I tell you?
AII will be well.

78
00:05:16.249 --> 00:05:17.999
-[all] Hey!
-[father] Oh! [laughs]

79
00:05:49.916 --> 00:05:50.874
Five thousand and three.

80
00:05:53.166 --> 00:05:54.166
Is that all?

81
00:05:54.582 --> 00:05:57.082
Yes, five thousand and three zlotys,
that's all we've got left.

82
00:05:57.249 --> 00:05:59.832
It's three thousand and three
zlotys too much. Look...

83
00:06:00.666 --> 00:06:04.041
[Regina] "Re: Further restrictions
regarding liquid assets.

84
00:06:04.207 --> 00:06:07.457
Jews will be allowed to keep a maximum
of two thousand zlotys in their homes."

85
00:06:07.916 --> 00:06:12.124
-[mother] What do we do with the rest?
-Deposit it in a bank. A blocked account.

86
00:06:12.291 --> 00:06:16.207
Banks? Who'd be stupid enough
to deposit money in a German bank?

87
00:06:16.291 --> 00:06:21.291
We could hide the money. Look here. We can
hide the money under the flowerpot.

88
00:06:21.374 --> 00:06:24.374
No, no, no. I’ll tell you what we’ll do.
We’ll use tried and tested methods.

89
00:06:24.457 --> 00:06:26.041
You know what we did in the last war?

90
00:06:27.041 --> 00:06:29.499
We made a hole in the table leg...
[taps the table leg]

91
00:06:29.582 --> 00:06:30.916
And we hid the money in there.

92
00:06:31.082 --> 00:06:33.707
-And suppose they take the table away?
-What do you mean take the table away?

93
00:06:33.791 --> 00:06:36.249
The Germans go into Jewish homes
and they just take what they want...

94
00:06:36.332 --> 00:06:38.541
furniture, valuables, anything.

95
00:06:38.624 --> 00:06:40.416
-[mother] Do they?
-Idiot! What would they want with a table.

96
00:06:40.499 --> 00:06:41.374
Hey? A table like this?

97
00:06:41.541 --> 00:06:42.457
[all gasp]

98
00:06:42.624 --> 00:06:45.291
-What on earth are you doing?
-No, listen, look.

99
00:06:45.957 --> 00:06:47.499
[Halina] This is the best place for it.

100
00:06:47.582 --> 00:06:49.582
[Halina] No-one would think of looking
under the flowerpot.

101
00:06:50.082 --> 00:06:51.916
No, no. No, no.
Listen, listen, I've been thinking--

102
00:06:52.082 --> 00:06:53.416
Oh! Really? That's a change.

103
00:06:53.499 --> 00:06:56.291
-You know what we do? We use psychology.
-[Wladek] We use what?

104
00:06:56.874 --> 00:06:58.749
We leave the money
and the watch on the table...

105
00:06:59.374 --> 00:07:01.624
and we cover it like this. In full view.

106
00:07:02.499 --> 00:07:04.041
[Halina laughs]

107
00:07:04.207 --> 00:07:05.166
Are you stupid?

108
00:07:05.249 --> 00:07:07.624
The Germans will search high and low,
I promise you, they’ll never notice.

109
00:07:07.791 --> 00:07:11.207
That's the stupidest thing I've ever seen.
Of course, they’ll notice it. Look.

110
00:07:12.291 --> 00:07:15.666
Look here... Idiot.

111
00:07:15.749 --> 00:07:17.541
[Henryk laughs] And you call me stupid.

112
00:07:17.624 --> 00:07:19.499
No, that is very good
because that is the last place--

113
00:07:19.666 --> 00:07:22.041
-This would take hours.
-We are not in a hurry. We'd get it back.

114
00:07:22.207 --> 00:07:24.124
-It won't take hours.
-How will you get them out? Tell me that!

115
00:07:24.207 --> 00:07:26.041
Tell me that, I would like to know.
How would you get them out?

116
00:07:26.124 --> 00:07:27.749
-Why do you resist?
-[Regina] Quiet! Order, please!

117
00:07:27.916 --> 00:07:29.666
-You take each one out individually.
-[Regina] Order please!

118
00:07:29.832 --> 00:07:31.291
No-one listens to me, no one listens.

119
00:07:31.457 --> 00:07:34.374
Quiet, please, quiet!
Order, order, please!

120
00:07:34.541 --> 00:07:38.374
-She's a lawyer, she likes order.
-Listen, just listen. Look,

121
00:07:38.457 --> 00:07:41.749
the watch we put under the flowerpots
and the money we stuff in the violin.

122
00:07:43.374 --> 00:07:44.499
Um...

123
00:07:44.666 --> 00:07:48.666
-Will I still be able to play?
-Well, you’ll find out.

124
00:07:49.457 --> 00:07:53.249
-Jurek? It's Wladek Szpilman.
<i>- Wladek, how are you?</i>

125
00:07:53.999 --> 00:07:56.291
Fine, fine, we're fine, thank you.
And you?

126
00:07:56.666 --> 00:08:00.999
<i>Elne, we're fine under the circumstances.
But I guess what you've called about.</i>

127
00:08:01.082 --> 00:08:03.499
<i>There’s nothing we can do.
They won't re-open the station.</i>

128
00:08:03.582 --> 00:08:05.041
<i>Just won't re-Open the station.</i>

129
00:08:05.541 --> 00:08:07.124
Yes, I know, but um, Jurek--

130
00:08:07.207 --> 00:08:09.624
<i>Not even music, nothing,
no radios nor the roles.</i>

131
00:08:09.707 --> 00:08:10.541
I know, Jurek!

132
00:08:10.624 --> 00:08:13.791
<i>But I'm sure you'll find work.
A pianist like you Wladek</i>

133
00:08:13.957 --> 00:08:16.374
Well, maybe, maybe not, but um...

134
00:08:16.957 --> 00:08:21.166
Listen, don't be offended, but I didn't
call to discuss my future career.

135
00:08:21.916 --> 00:08:25.166
I nagged Jurek for weeks and weeks,
and at last, he gave in and said...

136
00:08:25.249 --> 00:08:28.666
"AII right, come with me tomorrow",
And so I came and...

137
00:08:28.749 --> 00:08:30.666
they bombed the station.

138
00:08:31.499 --> 00:08:33.541
I tell you, meeting you like that
was absolutely wonderful.

139
00:08:34.124 --> 00:08:38.124
-Really?
-Yes, it was... It was unforgettable.

140
00:08:39.249 --> 00:08:41.207
I've always loved your playing,
Mr. Szpilman.

141
00:08:41.291 --> 00:08:42.332
Call me Wladek, please.

142
00:08:42.416 --> 00:08:45.374
-No-one plays Chopin like you.
-I hope that's a compliment.

143
00:08:45.832 --> 00:08:49.541
-Of course, I mean it.
-I was... trying to be funny.

144
00:08:50.374 --> 00:08:52.249
Shall we go to the Paradiso,
have a coffee?

145
00:08:52.332 --> 00:08:53.666
I'd like that.

146
00:08:55.457 --> 00:08:59.416
-And you, what do you do?
-I finished with the conservatoire.

147
00:08:59.499 --> 00:09:02.416
-You're a musician?
-Yes. But only just.

148
00:09:02.666 --> 00:09:04.291
-What instrument?
-The cello.

149
00:09:05.416 --> 00:09:07.332
I love to see a women playing the cello.

150
00:09:08.874 --> 00:09:09.874
Here we are.

151
00:09:10.957 --> 00:09:12.374
NO JEWS

152
00:09:12.457 --> 00:09:15.499
This is disgraceful. How dare they?

153
00:09:16.041 --> 00:09:18.791
You know what people are like,
they want to be better Nazis than Hitler.

154
00:09:18.874 --> 00:09:22.582
-I'm going in there to complain.
-No. It's better not, believe me.

155
00:09:23.082 --> 00:09:26.416
-It's so humiliating. Someone like you!
-[woman] Good-bye!

156
00:09:31.082 --> 00:09:32.332
We’ll find somewhere else.

157
00:09:33.416 --> 00:09:36.249
-[Dorota] We can walk in the park.
-No, we can't.

158
00:09:36.957 --> 00:09:40.457
It's an official decree.
No Jews allowed in the park.

159
00:09:41.124 --> 00:09:43.874
-My God. Are you joking?
-I'm not joking, it's true.

160
00:09:44.041 --> 00:09:47.124
I suggest we just sit on a bench somewhere
but that's another official decree,

161
00:09:47.207 --> 00:09:48.707
"no Jews allowed on public benches".

162
00:09:49.082 --> 00:09:50.541
This is absurd!

163
00:09:50.999 --> 00:09:54.041
I’ll tell you what we can do.
We can just stand here and talk.

164
00:09:54.541 --> 00:09:56.624
I think we're allowed to do that,
don't you?

165
00:09:57.916 --> 00:10:00.332
So, you play the cello Dorota.
That's nice.

166
00:10:00.957 --> 00:10:04.832
And who's your favorite composer?
Chopin? Really? Well...

167
00:10:05.291 --> 00:10:07.749
you’ll have to learn to play
his cello sonata, won't you?

168
00:10:08.207 --> 00:10:10.874
And what about you, Wladek? Well...

169
00:10:11.124 --> 00:10:13.791
Perhaps I could accompany you.
Me on the piano, you on the cello.

170
00:10:14.374 --> 00:10:17.624
Oh, Mr. Szpilman, you're quite,
quite wonderful.

171
00:10:20.374 --> 00:10:22.416
Call me Wladek, please.

172
00:10:22.832 --> 00:10:25.999
"Re: emblems for Jews
in the Warsaw district.

173
00:10:26.541 --> 00:10:29.666
I hereby order that all Jews
in the Warsaw district...

174
00:10:29.749 --> 00:10:32.749
will wear visible emblems
when out of doors.

175
00:10:33.291 --> 00:10:38.082
This decree will come into force
on the 1st of December, 1939...

176
00:10:38.166 --> 00:10:41.166
and applies to all Jews
over 1 2 years of age.

177
00:10:41.957 --> 00:10:44.832
The emblem will be worn
on the right sleeve...

178
00:10:45.416 --> 00:10:49.166
and will represent a blue star
of David on a white background.

179
00:10:49.832 --> 00:10:52.916
The background must
be sufficiently large...

180
00:10:52.999 --> 00:10:56.749
for the star to measure eight
centimeters from point to point.

181
00:10:57.374 --> 00:11:01.041
The width of the arms of the star
must be one centimeter.

182
00:11:01.666 --> 00:11:06.832
The Jews that do not respect this
decree will be severely punished.

183
00:11:07.207 --> 00:11:12.041
Governor of Warsaw district,
Dr. Fischer."

184
00:11:15.124 --> 00:11:16.166
I won't wear it.

185
00:11:16.249 --> 00:11:18.832
I won't wear it.
I'm not going to be branded.

186
00:11:23.249 --> 00:11:24.707
[clears throat] Let, let me see this.

187
00:11:29.416 --> 00:11:33.082
Does it say that we have to provide
these armbands ourselves?

188
00:11:34.291 --> 00:11:36.791
-Where will we get them?
-We're not going to get them.

189
00:11:36.874 --> 00:11:38.874
We're not going to wear them!

190
00:11:39.041 --> 00:11:40.374
[tram bell rings]

191
00:11:47.624 --> 00:11:48.666
[in German] You!

192
00:11:50.624 --> 00:11:51.916
[in German] Come here.

193
00:11:58.832 --> 00:12:00.666
[in German] Why didn't you bow?

194
00:12:02.082 --> 00:12:03.541
[in German] I beg your pardon.

195
00:12:04.541 --> 00:12:05.416
[father groans]

196
00:12:14.499 --> 00:12:16.541
[in German]
You're forbidden to walk on the pavement.

197
00:12:17.749 --> 00:12:19.249
[in German] Walk in the gutter!

198
00:12:36.291 --> 00:12:40.249
-Have you seen this?
-What, what, what? I'm working. What?

199
00:12:41.999 --> 00:12:43.332
What is it?

200
00:12:44.874 --> 00:12:47.791
-That's where they're going to put us.
-What do you mean, put us?

201
00:12:50.832 --> 00:12:54.666
"By order of the governor of the
Warsaw district, Dr. Fischer...

202
00:12:54.749 --> 00:12:58.166
concerning the establishment of
the Jewish district in Warsaw.

203
00:12:58.457 --> 00:13:02.082
There will be created a Jewish district
in which all Jews living in Warsaw

204
00:13:02.166 --> 00:13:04.332
or moving to Warsaw will have to reside."

205
00:13:05.124 --> 00:13:08.957
Look here. "Jews living outside
of the prescribed area

206
00:13:09.041 --> 00:13:14.291
will have to move to the Jewish
district by 31st of October, 1 940."

207
00:13:15.707 --> 00:13:20.124
They won't get all of us. It's too small.
There's 400 thousand of us in Warsaw.

208
00:13:20.291 --> 00:13:23.166
No, 360 thousand. So it will be easy.

209
00:13:23.957 --> 00:13:27.457
[mother crying]
What am I supposed to do? Hm? You tell me.

210
00:13:27.541 --> 00:13:29.916
[mother crying] You're a clever man,
you’ll tell me what I will buy.

211
00:13:29.999 --> 00:13:30.999
[father] I do my best.

212
00:13:31.457 --> 00:13:32.457
[Halina] Mama?

213
00:13:34.124 --> 00:13:36.832
Mama, what is it?

214
00:13:36.999 --> 00:13:39.707
[mother cries] 20 zlotys!

215
00:13:41.499 --> 00:13:44.416
That's all we have left, 20 zlotys.

216
00:13:47.291 --> 00:13:50.874
What, what can I buy with 20 zlotys?

217
00:13:52.374 --> 00:13:56.249
I am sick of cooking potatoes,
potatoes, potatoes.

218
00:14:04.457 --> 00:14:06.791
That's the price.
That's what I'm offering.

219
00:14:06.874 --> 00:14:09.749
My advice is to accept.
You won't get more from anyone else.

220
00:14:09.832 --> 00:14:13.749
-But, it's a Bechstein, Mr. Lipa!
-Two thousand. My advice is to take it.

221
00:14:14.124 --> 00:14:16.332
[Mr. Lipa] What are you going to do when
you're hungry? Eat the piano?

222
00:14:17.624 --> 00:14:20.124
-Get out!
-Hey! What's the matter with you?

223
00:14:20.291 --> 00:14:22.332
-Stop it!
-We'd rather give it away. Go on, get out!

224
00:14:22.416 --> 00:14:24.874
Haven't you eaten today? Hm?
What are you suffering from?

225
00:14:26.332 --> 00:14:27.666
You people are crazy.

226
00:14:29.166 --> 00:14:32.874
I'm doing you a favor. Two thousand
and I'm paying for the removal.

227
00:14:32.957 --> 00:14:34.749
I'm not even charging for the removal!

228
00:14:36.624 --> 00:14:38.791
You haven't eaten today. You're crazy.

229
00:14:39.166 --> 00:14:40.291
Take it.

230
00:15:15.499 --> 00:15:16.499
[Wladek] Hello.

231
00:15:18.582 --> 00:15:19.832
Hello. Hi.

232
00:15:22.749 --> 00:15:24.416
I didn't want to come.

233
00:15:25.249 --> 00:15:29.916
I didn't want to see all this, but...
I couldn't stop myself.

234
00:15:30.082 --> 00:15:32.249
-How are you doing?
-Fine.

235
00:15:32.332 --> 00:15:33.499
Good.

236
00:15:34.457 --> 00:15:37.374
No, not really. They arrested my cousin.

237
00:15:38.332 --> 00:15:40.249
Jurek says they’ll let him out.

238
00:15:41.999 --> 00:15:46.124
-This is disgraceful.
-It won't last long. Don't worry.

239
00:15:46.707 --> 00:15:48.791
That's what I said myself.

240
00:15:50.249 --> 00:15:51.707
It's too absurd.

241
00:15:56.707 --> 00:15:59.291
I ah... I should go.

242
00:16:01.749 --> 00:16:04.207
Well, I’ll, I’ll see you...

243
00:16:05.166 --> 00:16:06.166
soon.

244
00:16:10.957 --> 00:16:12.124
Goodbye.

245
00:16:27.499 --> 00:16:28.916
Well...

246
00:16:29.666 --> 00:16:33.457
to tell you the truth,
I thought it would be worse.

247
00:16:39.999 --> 00:16:43.916
-Where will we sleep?
-I sleep in the kitchen with the girls.

248
00:16:44.582 --> 00:16:47.082
You, Henryk and papa, in here.

249
00:16:49.166 --> 00:16:50.374
Look.

250
00:16:52.332 --> 00:16:53.707
Come and look.

251
00:16:58.874 --> 00:17:01.041
[somber orchestral music playing]

252
00:17:20.374 --> 00:17:22.374
[indistinct chatter]

253
00:17:27.124 --> 00:17:30.499
Go away. Go away! Go away!

254
00:17:32.541 --> 00:17:36.082
Papa! Papa! Papa!

255
00:17:51.416 --> 00:17:55.082
-Sell anything?
-Just one. Dostoyevsky, <i>The Idiot.</i>

256
00:17:55.166 --> 00:17:57.916
-Three zlotys.
-It's better than yesterday.

257
00:17:57.999 --> 00:18:02.332
Three lousy zlotys. And there are
people there making millions.

258
00:18:02.416 --> 00:18:04.874
-I know.
-You don't know, believe me.

259
00:18:05.541 --> 00:18:08.499
They bribe the guards,
the guards turn a blind eye.

260
00:18:08.957 --> 00:18:13.749
They're bringing in cartloads of food,
tobacco, liquor, French cosmetics.

261
00:18:13.999 --> 00:18:15.832
And the poor are dying all around
and they don't give a damn.

262
00:18:15.999 --> 00:18:19.791
Excuse me, have you seen
my husband, Izaak Szerman?

263
00:18:20.499 --> 00:18:24.124
A tall, a tall handsome man,
with a little gray beard... No?

264
00:18:24.374 --> 00:18:29.041
-I'm afraid not.
-Excuse me. Goodbye.

265
00:18:29.124 --> 00:18:32.832
Sleep well. But, but, but if you see him,
write to me, yes?

266
00:18:33.666 --> 00:18:35.082
Izaak Szerman.

267
00:18:35.249 --> 00:18:37.207
[tram bell rings]

268
00:18:49.957 --> 00:18:53.332
Why do we have to have a gentile
street running through our area?

269
00:18:53.416 --> 00:18:55.249
Why can't they go around?

270
00:18:55.749 --> 00:18:59.457
Don't worry about it. They're about
to build a bridge. Haven't you heard?

271
00:19:00.374 --> 00:19:02.541
A bridge, a bridge a smedge.

272
00:19:03.666 --> 00:19:06.249
[Jewish man]
The Germans claim to be intelligent.

273
00:19:06.332 --> 00:19:09.624
But do you know what I think?
I think they are totally stupid.

274
00:19:10.207 --> 00:19:13.666
I have a family to feed.
I spend half of my time here

275
00:19:13.749 --> 00:19:15.707
waiting for them to let us through.

276
00:19:16.374 --> 00:19:19.124
[Jewish man] Maybe they think I come
here to listen to the music?

277
00:19:19.291 --> 00:19:21.541
[speaking German]

278
00:19:22.166 --> 00:19:24.166
[in German] You're cold?

279
00:19:24.624 --> 00:19:26.999
[speaking German]

280
00:19:27.374 --> 00:19:28.624
[in German] Dance!

281
00:19:29.124 --> 00:19:31.291
-[in German] Dance!
-[in German] Dance!

282
00:19:31.374 --> 00:19:34.916
[in German] Come on, come on! Dance!

283
00:19:38.166 --> 00:19:41.582
[speaking German]

284
00:19:43.541 --> 00:19:47.624
[speaking German]

285
00:19:51.124 --> 00:19:53.374
[speaking German]

286
00:19:58.624 --> 00:19:59.874
[soldier speaking German]

287
00:20:02.707 --> 00:20:03.957
[in German] Faster!

288
00:20:05.374 --> 00:20:07.541
[speaking German]

289
00:20:09.249 --> 00:20:10.541
[soldier speaking German]

290
00:20:14.082 --> 00:20:15.166
[speaking German]

291
00:20:17.791 --> 00:20:18.957
[soldier speaking German]

292
00:20:21.457 --> 00:20:26.166
[soldiers speaking German]

293
00:20:26.416 --> 00:20:29.416
[soldiers speaking German]
[whistle blows]

294
00:20:48.457 --> 00:20:49.416
[mother] Good, they're here.

295
00:20:51.916 --> 00:20:53.999
Yitzchak Heller's been waiting for you.

296
00:21:01.166 --> 00:21:02.666
-What's this about?
-[mother] Sit down, have tea.

297
00:21:02.832 --> 00:21:05.249
[mother] I’ll start lunch
when the girls get here.

298
00:21:11.499 --> 00:21:14.541
-[Henryk] So, what are you doing here?
-[father] He brought cakes.

299
00:21:14.624 --> 00:21:18.332
His ah... his father's back
in the jewelry business.

300
00:21:18.416 --> 00:21:20.332
He's, uh, doing well, hey, Yitzchak, hey?

301
00:21:21.374 --> 00:21:22.332
[father chuckles]

302
00:21:23.124 --> 00:21:24.749
[father] Amazing, jewelry.

303
00:21:25.874 --> 00:21:27.999
-We're recruiting.
-Who is recruiting?

304
00:21:28.082 --> 00:21:30.207
Don't be clever with me, Henryk.
I'm coming as a friend.

305
00:21:30.999 --> 00:21:32.957
[Heller] They're bringing Jews
in from all over the country.

306
00:21:33.124 --> 00:21:34.916
Soon there will be half million
people in the ghetto.

307
00:21:35.332 --> 00:21:39.249
-We need more Jewish police.
-Oh! More Jewish police!

308
00:21:39.332 --> 00:21:43.082
You mean you want me to beat up Jews with
my truncheon and catch the Gestapo spirit.

309
00:21:43.249 --> 00:21:44.957
-[Henryk] I see!
-Someone's got to do it, Henryk.

310
00:21:45.041 --> 00:21:45.832
[Henryk] But why me?

311
00:21:45.999 --> 00:21:48.416
I thought you only recruited
boys with rich fathers.

312
00:21:48.666 --> 00:21:50.832
Look at my father, look at us, I mean.

313
00:21:50.999 --> 00:21:52.541
Yes, I'm looking at you,
that's why I'm here.

314
00:21:52.624 --> 00:21:53.957
Your whole family can have a better life.

315
00:21:54.041 --> 00:21:56.416
You want to go on struggling for survival,
selling books on the street?

316
00:21:56.499 --> 00:21:57.624
Yes, please.

317
00:21:57.791 --> 00:22:00.457
[scoffs] I'm doing you people a favor.

318
00:22:01.666 --> 00:22:03.874
What about you, Wladek?
You're a great pianist.

319
00:22:03.957 --> 00:22:05.541
And we've got an excellent
police jazz band.

320
00:22:05.707 --> 00:22:07.291
They'd welcome you with open arms.
Join us!

321
00:22:07.374 --> 00:22:09.666
-[Heller] You've got no work.
-Thank you, I've got work.

322
00:22:13.082 --> 00:22:14.999
[noisy chatter and laughter]

323
00:22:53.499 --> 00:22:55.499
[indistinct conversation]

324
00:22:55.874 --> 00:22:57.166
Yes of course!

325
00:22:59.457 --> 00:23:01.332
I'm sorry, Wladek, he wants you to stop.

326
00:23:03.874 --> 00:23:05.249
[continues playing]
Who wants me to stop?

327
00:23:14.207 --> 00:23:16.207
[Wladek stops playing]
[noisy indistinct chatter continues]

328
00:23:42.416 --> 00:23:44.416
[Wladek continues playing]

329
00:23:52.666 --> 00:23:53.666
[small dog barks]

330
00:23:57.624 --> 00:23:59.291
[Jehuda] I always say,
Look on the bright side.

331
00:23:59.749 --> 00:24:02.916
[Jehuda] You're in a small ghetto with
intellectuals, professional people.

332
00:24:02.999 --> 00:24:06.749
[Jehuda] You're better off than us.
Here in the large ghetto it's a cesspool.

333
00:24:06.832 --> 00:24:08.207
Jehuda, give me something to do.

334
00:24:08.374 --> 00:24:12.374
You're an artist, Wladek. You keep
peoples' spirits up. You do enough.

335
00:24:12.457 --> 00:24:15.832
-I want to help, I want to do something.
-You're too well known, Wladek.

336
00:24:16.166 --> 00:24:21.332
And you know what? You musicians
don't make good conspirators.

337
00:24:21.416 --> 00:24:25.499
You're too... too... musical.
[laughs]

338
00:24:31.332 --> 00:24:32.541
-Who is that?
-Symche.

339
00:24:32.624 --> 00:24:33.749
[Symche] Majorek.

340
00:24:35.666 --> 00:24:39.207
[Wladek] There are notices going up.
City is to be cleansed of undesirables.

341
00:24:39.291 --> 00:24:42.291
-No notices going up.
-[Majorek] Hello, Symche.

342
00:24:43.291 --> 00:24:46.166
Dolek... Mrs. Zyskind.

343
00:24:48.332 --> 00:24:50.374
[Majorek] Jehuda, working hard?

344
00:24:50.457 --> 00:24:54.666
Majorek. This is the greatest pianist
in Poland. Maybe the whole world.

345
00:24:54.749 --> 00:24:57.082
Wladyslaw Szpilman, meet Majorek.

346
00:24:57.332 --> 00:24:59.791
-How do you do?
-I know your name.

347
00:25:00.874 --> 00:25:03.541
-I've never heard you play.
-[Jehuda] Majorek used to be in the Army.

348
00:25:04.166 --> 00:25:07.791
Brilliant man. The only thing I've got
against him is he's not a socialist.

349
00:25:07.874 --> 00:25:09.457
[Jehuda laughs]

350
00:25:10.041 --> 00:25:12.582
[Jehuda] You better go now, Wladek.
It's nearly curfew.

351
00:25:14.416 --> 00:25:16.582
[Jehuda] You know how many copies
we print of our newspaper?

352
00:25:17.749 --> 00:25:18.999
[Jehuda] Five hundred.

353
00:25:19.749 --> 00:25:23.207
You know how many people on
average read one copy? Twenty.

354
00:25:23.291 --> 00:25:27.874
That makes ten thousand readers.
These will start the uprising.

355
00:25:27.957 --> 00:25:31.166
Majorek hides them in his underpants
and leaves them in toilets.

356
00:25:31.582 --> 00:25:33.832
-Toilets, huh?
-As many toilets as I can find.

357
00:25:34.582 --> 00:25:36.457
Germans never use Jewish toilets.

358
00:25:37.332 --> 00:25:40.082
-They're too clean for them.
-[Jehuda laughs]

359
00:25:40.957 --> 00:25:42.957
[indistinct chatter]

360
00:25:45.541 --> 00:25:48.207
[young beggar]
Please, Mister, please, one zloty.

361
00:25:48.374 --> 00:25:50.999
[dog barks]
[man whistles]

362
00:25:55.666 --> 00:25:57.041
[man whistles again]

363
00:26:05.041 --> 00:26:06.124
[boy speaks in German]

364
00:26:12.374 --> 00:26:14.166
[man shouts in German]

365
00:26:14.582 --> 00:26:16.582
[whack, screaming]

366
00:26:16.666 --> 00:26:18.499
[man in German] Hold it!
You little bastard!

367
00:26:18.582 --> 00:26:20.541
[screaming continues]

368
00:26:21.082 --> 00:26:24.332
[screaming continues]
[man continues speaking in German]

369
00:26:24.874 --> 00:26:26.249
[Wladek] Stop it! Stop it!

370
00:26:26.332 --> 00:26:27.291
[screaming continues]

371
00:26:27.374 --> 00:26:28.166
[Wladek] Stop it!

372
00:26:31.582 --> 00:26:34.832
[Wladek] Come on, come on, come on.
Come on boy.

373
00:26:36.874 --> 00:26:38.874
[man speaks in German]

374
00:26:40.874 --> 00:26:43.499
Stand up. Stand up. Stand up!

375
00:26:43.916 --> 00:26:45.874
[man speaks in German]

376
00:26:51.874 --> 00:26:54.166
[Wladek breathes heavily]

377
00:26:58.249 --> 00:27:00.166
[dog barks nearby]

378
00:27:12.249 --> 00:27:14.249
[footsteps approach]

379
00:27:14.874 --> 00:27:19.416
Please, tonight for once, I don't
want anything bad talked about.

380
00:27:19.499 --> 00:27:22.791
-Enjoy our meal.
-Fine, then I’ll tell you something funny.

381
00:27:23.207 --> 00:27:24.707
You all know who I mean by Dr. Raszeja?

382
00:27:24.874 --> 00:27:26.249
-The surgeon.
-[Henryk] The surgeon.

383
00:27:26.624 --> 00:27:28.541
[Henryk] Well, for some reason,
don't ask me why,

384
00:27:28.999 --> 00:27:31.582
the Germans allowed him into
the ghetto to perform an operation.

385
00:27:31.666 --> 00:27:34.957
On a Jew? They let a Pole
to come in to operate on a Jew?

386
00:27:35.041 --> 00:27:38.291
He got a pass, that's all I know.
Anyway, so he...

387
00:27:38.374 --> 00:27:40.707
he puts the patient to sleep
and starts the operation.

388
00:27:40.999 --> 00:27:43.541
He'd just made the first incision
when the SS burst in...

389
00:27:44.124 --> 00:27:45.624
shoot the patient lying on the table,

390
00:27:45.707 --> 00:27:48.291
then Dr. Raszeja and everybody
else who was there.

391
00:27:50.416 --> 00:27:51.332
Isn't that a laugh?

392
00:27:53.916 --> 00:27:57.041
The patient didn't feel a thing,
he was anesthetized. [laughs]

393
00:27:57.332 --> 00:27:59.207
I said nothing bad, Henryk.

394
00:27:59.832 --> 00:28:03.666
What's the matter with you all, huh?
Huh? You lost your sense of humor?

395
00:28:04.707 --> 00:28:05.874
It's not funny.

396
00:28:06.332 --> 00:28:10.124
Well, you know what's funny?
You're funny, with that ridiculous tie.

397
00:28:11.457 --> 00:28:14.499
What are you talking about my tie for?
What's my tie have to do with anything?

398
00:28:14.666 --> 00:28:16.999
-[Wladek] I need this tie for my work.
-Your work?

399
00:28:17.166 --> 00:28:19.291
-Yes, that's right, I work.
-Yes, yes, your work.

400
00:28:19.374 --> 00:28:21.416
Playing the piano for all
the parasites in the ghetto.

401
00:28:21.582 --> 00:28:22.791
-Parasites?
-Parasites.

402
00:28:22.957 --> 00:28:24.249
Boys. Boys!

403
00:28:24.332 --> 00:28:25.749
They don't give a damn
about people's sufferings.

404
00:28:25.832 --> 00:28:27.416
And you blame me for their apathy, right?

405
00:28:27.499 --> 00:28:29.332
I do because I see it every day.

406
00:28:29.416 --> 00:28:31.291
They don't even notice
what's going around them.

407
00:28:31.374 --> 00:28:33.457
-I blame the Americans.
-For what? For my tie?

408
00:28:33.957 --> 00:28:36.249
The American Jews,
and there are lots of them.

409
00:28:37.582 --> 00:28:39.582
What have they done for us, hey?
What do they think they're doing?

410
00:28:39.666 --> 00:28:42.541
People here are dying.
Haven't got a bite to eat.

411
00:28:44.082 --> 00:28:46.207
The Jewish bankers over there
should be persuading America

412
00:28:46.291 --> 00:28:47.832
to declare war on Germany.

413
00:28:47.916 --> 00:28:50.916
[car tires squeal]
[engine revs]

414
00:29:05.749 --> 00:29:06.999
[whispers] Lights! Lights!

415
00:29:25.874 --> 00:29:29.166
[SS Officer speaking German]

416
00:29:32.749 --> 00:29:35.374
[SS Officer speaking German]

417
00:29:37.082 --> 00:29:38.374
[banging on door]

418
00:29:38.457 --> 00:29:42.707
[SS Officer speaking German]

419
00:29:44.916 --> 00:29:46.082
[SS Officer speaking German]

420
00:29:46.624 --> 00:29:51.041
[terrified woman speaking German]

421
00:30:00.666 --> 00:30:01.624
[SS Officer] Stand up!

422
00:30:04.874 --> 00:30:07.541
[SS Officer] You, stand up! Come on!

423
00:30:09.082 --> 00:30:10.499
[SS Officer] Throw him out!

424
00:30:22.124 --> 00:30:23.832
-[mother] Ah!
-[body thuds as it hits the pavement]

425
00:30:23.916 --> 00:30:27.082
Shhh. Shhh. Be quiet, Mama,
for God's sake, shhh, be quiet.

426
00:30:27.166 --> 00:30:28.207
[father] My God!

427
00:30:28.291 --> 00:30:30.291
[SS Officer speaking German]

428
00:30:35.166 --> 00:30:37.166
[mother continues crying]

429
00:30:39.374 --> 00:30:42.749
[SS Officer speaking German]

430
00:30:43.624 --> 00:30:44.874
[multiple gunshots]

431
00:30:59.999 --> 00:31:01.082
[gunshot]

432
00:31:02.957 --> 00:31:06.957
[engine starts]
[car doors slam]

433
00:31:11.124 --> 00:31:15.291
[man shouts in German]

434
00:31:23.624 --> 00:31:25.624
[crying]

435
00:31:27.874 --> 00:31:29.874
[playing piano]

436
00:31:42.582 --> 00:31:44.582
[beggar girl] Matches! Matches!

437
00:31:49.457 --> 00:31:50.291
-Excuse me!
-Yes!

438
00:31:50.374 --> 00:31:53.749
-I'm Mr. Szpilman's sister.
-Yes, come in. Not you!

439
00:31:54.374 --> 00:31:56.374
[piano playing]
[indistinct chatter]

440
00:32:13.749 --> 00:32:16.124
-What's happened?
-Oh my God, it's terrible.

441
00:32:16.207 --> 00:32:18.666
-What?
-They're hunting people in the streets.

442
00:32:19.207 --> 00:32:20.624
They've taken Henryk.

443
00:32:21.832 --> 00:32:22.832
[sighs heavily]

444
00:32:23.207 --> 00:32:26.041
AII right, go home, alright?
Go home, I’ll take care of it.

445
00:32:27.457 --> 00:32:29.374
[indistinct chatter]

446
00:32:37.874 --> 00:32:41.666
Excuse me. Have you seen
my husband? Izaak Szerman?

447
00:32:41.749 --> 00:32:45.749
-No, I'm afraid not.
-Tall, handsome, a little gray beard.

448
00:32:45.832 --> 00:32:49.624
If you see him, write to me.
Don't forget. Izaak Szerman.

449
00:32:49.791 --> 00:32:51.082
[whistle blows]

450
00:32:51.166 --> 00:32:53.124
[Jewish police in German]
Faster, keep moving! Run!

451
00:32:59.457 --> 00:33:00.666
What happened here?

452
00:33:01.249 --> 00:33:05.332
They've got my grandson in there.
They pick them up, they take them away.

453
00:33:05.416 --> 00:33:09.124
What they do to them,
I've stopped believing in God.

454
00:33:09.999 --> 00:33:12.457
Excuse me. Excuse me.

455
00:33:13.874 --> 00:33:14.999
[Wladek] Yitzchak?

456
00:33:16.666 --> 00:33:20.999
Yitzchak? Yitzchak, here,
it's Wladek Szpilman!

457
00:33:23.499 --> 00:33:24.374
[child cries]

458
00:33:24.541 --> 00:33:25.582
[woman] Here!

459
00:33:27.957 --> 00:33:30.624
-Henryk's in there.
-I haven't seen him.

460
00:33:30.707 --> 00:33:32.874
-Believe me. They picked him up.
-[Heller] Tough luck!

461
00:33:37.082 --> 00:33:37.957
Can you help?

462
00:33:38.124 --> 00:33:41.207
Oh, now you need me, yes, now you need me!

463
00:33:41.374 --> 00:33:42.499
Can you help us?

464
00:33:44.249 --> 00:33:46.957
-It costs.
-I have no money.

465
00:33:47.124 --> 00:33:47.957
Then there's nothing I can do.

466
00:33:48.041 --> 00:33:49.791
You should've joined us
when you had the chance.

467
00:33:49.957 --> 00:33:54.291
-Yitzchak they told me you had influence.
-Who told you?

468
00:33:55.499 --> 00:33:58.124
People, people I know.
They said you're an important man.

469
00:34:00.749 --> 00:34:01.666
[Wladek] Yitzchak!

470
00:34:09.832 --> 00:34:10.791
[whistle blows]

471
00:34:10.957 --> 00:34:13.291
[man shouts in German]

472
00:34:15.999 --> 00:34:18.207
[Rubinstein speaking Yiddish]

473
00:34:19.041 --> 00:34:22.124
-[1 st Shupo] Who is this?
-[2nd Shupo] Good morning Herr Rubinstein.

474
00:34:22.207 --> 00:34:26.041
-[1st Shupo] Good morning.
-[Rubinstein speaking Yiddish]

475
00:34:26.124 --> 00:34:28.416
-[Rubinstein] <i>Kaputt. Kaputt.</i>
-[German officers laugh]

476
00:34:28.499 --> 00:34:31.832
-[Officers speaking German]
-[Rubinstein speaking Yiddish]

477
00:34:31.916 --> 00:34:35.416
-[2nd Shupo] Want a cigarette?
-[Rubinstein] Cigarette? Mmm.

478
00:34:35.499 --> 00:34:37.124
[Rubinstein in German] Thank you.

479
00:34:39.207 --> 00:34:43.124
[Rubinstein speaking Yiddish]

480
00:34:43.374 --> 00:34:45.624
-[2nd Shupo speaking German]
-[both laugh]

481
00:34:45.707 --> 00:34:48.666
[Rubinstein speaking Yiddish]

482
00:34:48.749 --> 00:34:52.624
[Rubinstein speaking Yiddish]

483
00:34:52.707 --> 00:34:57.666
[Rubinstein speaking Yiddish]

484
00:34:59.957 --> 00:35:06.582
Help! Help! Help! Help! A snatcher!
A snatcher! Help, help me!

485
00:35:15.624 --> 00:35:17.332
[woman cries]

486
00:35:32.791 --> 00:35:34.791
[man speaks indistinctly]

487
00:35:59.374 --> 00:36:02.582
-Why did they pick you up?
-So, you go to Yitzchak Heller?

488
00:36:02.999 --> 00:36:06.666
-Did I ask you to talk to him?
-You're out, aren't you?

489
00:36:06.749 --> 00:36:09.624
Did you beg, did you grovel to
that piece of shit, that cockroach?

490
00:36:09.707 --> 00:36:11.582
I didn't grovel, I asked him to help you.

491
00:36:12.332 --> 00:36:13.582
What did you pay him?

492
00:36:15.541 --> 00:36:17.957
With what, with what could I pay him?
With what?

493
00:36:18.041 --> 00:36:20.207
Every zloty I earn we spend on food.

494
00:36:20.291 --> 00:36:23.457
-I can look after myself.
-They were taking you away.

495
00:36:23.541 --> 00:36:27.332
It's got nothing to do with you.
It's me they wanted, not you.

496
00:36:27.582 --> 00:36:30.499
Why do you have to interfere
with other people's business?

497
00:36:31.082 --> 00:36:32.999
You're mad. That's,
that's your trouble, is your mad.

498
00:36:33.082 --> 00:36:34.999
That's also my business.

499
00:36:35.082 --> 00:36:36.541
[tram bell rings]

500
00:36:42.082 --> 00:36:47.124
Hey, hey! What's the matter?
What's the matter? Are you sick?

501
00:36:48.749 --> 00:36:50.207
Hungry.

502
00:36:54.624 --> 00:36:56.499
[doorman] Mr. Szpilman!

503
00:36:58.416 --> 00:37:02.666
Employment certificate? What's that
mean, no employment certificate?

504
00:37:02.916 --> 00:37:05.874
You have to have an
employment certificate...

505
00:37:05.957 --> 00:37:08.749
to work for one of the German firms
in the ghetto, otherwise...

506
00:37:08.916 --> 00:37:11.707
-Otherwise, what?
-[Henryk] You'll be deported.

507
00:37:11.791 --> 00:37:15.041
-So, the rumors were true.
-[Henryk] They're going to resettle us...

508
00:37:16.166 --> 00:37:18.832
and send us to Iabor camps, in the East.

509
00:37:21.207 --> 00:37:23.666
-And they're closing the small ghetto.
-My God!

510
00:37:25.582 --> 00:37:27.582
[street noise]
[indistinct chatter]

511
00:37:39.582 --> 00:37:41.541
[Jehuda] Wladek? Wladek?

512
00:37:42.499 --> 00:37:46.499
I thought you'd be off on tour playing
London, Paris, New York, Chicago.

513
00:37:46.582 --> 00:37:48.416
-Not this week.
-You look terrible.

514
00:37:49.749 --> 00:37:52.582
Have you heard the rumors?
They're going to resettle us in the East.

515
00:37:52.666 --> 00:37:56.707
Rumors! You take it all too much
to heart Wladek. What's the trouble?

516
00:37:57.124 --> 00:38:00.749
I, I've been trying to get the
certificate of employment for my father.

517
00:38:01.499 --> 00:38:03.707
But I managed to get one for me
and the rest of my family,

518
00:38:03.791 --> 00:38:05.166
but I need another one for my father.

519
00:38:05.249 --> 00:38:07.749
-I've been to all the firms and shops...
-Why didn't you come to me?

520
00:38:08.749 --> 00:38:10.832
I didn't know you were
in the certificate business.

521
00:38:10.916 --> 00:38:12.582
I'm not, but Majorek is.

522
00:38:15.624 --> 00:38:17.541
Can you help? I have no money.

523
00:38:17.624 --> 00:38:21.082
Please, don't insult us.
Can you do something for him?

524
00:38:21.624 --> 00:38:24.124
Be at the Schultz workshop tomorrow,
four o'clock.

525
00:38:24.291 --> 00:38:27.082
You see what a wonderful piece
of luck you've had today?

526
00:38:27.166 --> 00:38:31.124
That's the historical imperative
in action! That's why I always say:

527
00:38:31.207 --> 00:38:33.749
-Look on the bright side!
-The bright side, yes, I know.

528
00:38:33.916 --> 00:38:35.791
[roar of sowing machines]

529
00:38:46.707 --> 00:38:49.041
-[Majorek] How's your back?
-Better.

530
00:38:49.499 --> 00:38:50.499
Better?

531
00:38:51.666 --> 00:38:53.207
Better not ask!

532
00:39:06.666 --> 00:39:12.041
-Thank you.
-My pleasure. Won't help you anyway.

533
00:39:12.207 --> 00:39:14.124
[Schultz laughs]

534
00:39:14.207 --> 00:39:15.749
[Majorek] Thank you, Mr. Schultz.

535
00:39:24.249 --> 00:39:26.249
[sorrowful orchestral music]

536
00:39:37.582 --> 00:39:38.874
[tram bell rings]

537
00:39:46.457 --> 00:39:48.291
[tram bell rings]

538
00:39:54.874 --> 00:39:56.541
[indistinct chatter]

539
00:40:27.707 --> 00:40:29.791
Well, at least we got work in the ghetto.
Hey?

540
00:40:31.666 --> 00:40:33.166
At least we are still together.

541
00:40:34.374 --> 00:40:36.124
[gunshot]
[woman screams]

542
00:40:36.291 --> 00:40:37.999
[German voices shouting]

543
00:40:39.082 --> 00:40:40.957
[gunshot]
[woman screams]

544
00:40:41.041 --> 00:40:43.082
[man shouts in German]

545
00:40:43.166 --> 00:40:46.541
[gunshot]
[man shouts in German]

546
00:40:48.124 --> 00:40:50.291
AII out! Into the yard!

547
00:40:50.791 --> 00:40:51.666
[shouting in German]

548
00:40:53.999 --> 00:40:57.791
We're all employed.
We've got work permits.

549
00:41:02.166 --> 00:41:04.291
-Wait.
-[gunshot]

550
00:41:05.041 --> 00:41:05.999
Here.

551
00:41:06.166 --> 00:41:08.582
[German NCO in German]
Go over there. Hurry.

552
00:41:09.624 --> 00:41:10.541
[German NCO in German] You.

553
00:41:11.999 --> 00:41:14.332
[German NCO in German] You. You.

554
00:41:16.499 --> 00:41:17.499
[German NCO in German] You.

555
00:41:19.874 --> 00:41:20.999
[German NCO in German] You.

556
00:41:23.291 --> 00:41:24.416
[German NCO in German] You.

557
00:41:34.166 --> 00:41:37.666
[in German] The rest of you,
get dressed and report back here!

558
00:41:37.749 --> 00:41:40.082
Bring your belongings, only 1 5 kilos!

559
00:41:40.999 --> 00:41:43.166
Where are you taking us?

560
00:41:48.999 --> 00:41:50.041
[baby cries]

561
00:42:07.916 --> 00:42:09.374
I'm sorry, I did my best.

562
00:42:12.707 --> 00:42:14.541
I thought the certificates would save us.

563
00:42:14.707 --> 00:42:15.707
Stop it, Wladek.

564
00:42:15.791 --> 00:42:19.291
Let's just hope that Henryk
and Halina will be better off.

565
00:42:28.791 --> 00:42:31.041
[German officers speaking indistinctly]

566
00:42:37.457 --> 00:42:39.249
[German officer speaking indistinctly]

567
00:42:43.624 --> 00:42:44.874
[Jewish policeman #1 ] Move on!

568
00:42:45.249 --> 00:42:46.541
[Jewish policeman #2] Come on, come on!

569
00:42:47.166 --> 00:42:49.582
-Where will we be going?
-You're going to work.

570
00:42:49.666 --> 00:42:52.749
You'll be much better off than
in the stinking ghetto. Move.

571
00:42:57.541 --> 00:43:01.374
[young woman] Why did I do it?
Why did I do it?

572
00:43:02.666 --> 00:43:07.707
[young woman] Why did I do it?
Why did I do it?

573
00:43:09.624 --> 00:43:11.499
Why did I do it?

574
00:43:16.624 --> 00:43:21.874
[young woman] Why did I do it?
Why did I do it? Why did I do it?

575
00:43:23.916 --> 00:43:25.916
[young woman] Why did I do it?

576
00:43:26.291 --> 00:43:28.291
[indistinct chatter]
[baby cries]

577
00:43:28.624 --> 00:43:30.624
[young woman cries]

578
00:43:39.374 --> 00:43:41.374
[woman cries]

579
00:43:48.499 --> 00:43:51.041
[woman with child] I beg you,
don't you have a drop of water?

580
00:43:55.957 --> 00:43:58.624
Don't you have a drop of water?
He's dying.

581
00:43:59.249 --> 00:44:00.999
My child is dying of thirst.

582
00:44:01.082 --> 00:44:02.874
-I beg you. I beg you.
-I'm sorry.

583
00:44:02.957 --> 00:44:05.791
Don't you have a drop of water?
I beg you.

584
00:44:05.874 --> 00:44:06.749
[Dr. Szpilman]
Did you hear what I'm saying?

585
00:44:06.916 --> 00:44:09.332
-I'm telling you, it's a disgrace.
-I can hear you.

586
00:44:09.416 --> 00:44:11.957
[Dr. Szpilman] We're letting them take us
to our death like sheep to the slaughter.

587
00:44:12.041 --> 00:44:13.916
-Not so loud.
-[Dr. Szpilman] Why don't we attack them?

588
00:44:14.457 --> 00:44:17.041
There's half a million of us here.
We can break out of the ghetto.

589
00:44:17.791 --> 00:44:20.457
At least we can die honorably,
not as a stain on the face of history.

590
00:44:20.624 --> 00:44:22.791
Why are you so sure they're
sending us to our death?

591
00:44:22.874 --> 00:44:25.874
I'm not sure. You know why I'm not sure?
Because they didn't tell me.

592
00:44:26.457 --> 00:44:27.999
But I'm telling you,
they're going to wipe us all out.

593
00:44:28.166 --> 00:44:30.666
Dr. Ehrlich, what do you want me to do?
Do you want me to fight?

594
00:44:30.749 --> 00:44:33.416
To fight, you need organization,
plans, guns.

595
00:44:33.499 --> 00:44:36.416
[father] He's right. What do you think I
can do? Fight them with my violin bow?

596
00:44:36.582 --> 00:44:39.166
The Germans would never squander
a huge Iabor force like this.

597
00:44:39.957 --> 00:44:41.832
They're sending us to a Iabor camp,
it's obvious.

598
00:44:41.916 --> 00:44:42.999
Oh, sure.

599
00:44:43.457 --> 00:44:46.416
Look at that cripple there,
look at the old people, the children.

600
00:44:46.499 --> 00:44:47.499
They're going to work?

601
00:44:48.124 --> 00:44:51.291
Look at you! Well, you're going to carry
iron girders on your back?

602
00:45:01.499 --> 00:45:03.916
[noisy indistinct chatter]

603
00:45:34.124 --> 00:45:37.124
Henryk! Halina, Henryk!

604
00:45:37.291 --> 00:45:39.666
[mother] Halina! Henryk!

605
00:45:42.374 --> 00:45:46.541
-[Halina cries]
-[Regina] Oh my God!

606
00:45:46.957 --> 00:45:51.082
We heard you were here.
we wanted to be with you!

607
00:46:00.416 --> 00:46:01.874
We wanted to be with you!

608
00:46:02.041 --> 00:46:05.332
[sighs] Stupid. Stupid.

609
00:46:05.499 --> 00:46:09.624
[young woman] Why did I do it?
Why did I do it?

610
00:46:09.707 --> 00:46:11.749
She's getting on my nerves.

611
00:46:17.041 --> 00:46:21.707
-What did she do, for God's sake?
-She smothered her baby.

612
00:46:23.957 --> 00:46:27.082
They prepared a hiding place
and of course they went there.

613
00:46:28.166 --> 00:46:30.749
But the baby cried
just as the police came.

614
00:46:31.166 --> 00:46:35.124
She smothered the cries with
her hands, the baby died.

615
00:46:36.582 --> 00:46:39.999
[Grun] A policeman heard the death rattle
and found where they were hiding.

616
00:46:41.124 --> 00:46:43.124
[woman crying]

617
00:46:47.832 --> 00:46:49.832
[indistinct chatter]

618
00:47:05.416 --> 00:47:06.707
What are you reading?

619
00:47:10.082 --> 00:47:15.082
"If you prick us, de we not bleed?
If you tickle us, do we not laugh?

620
00:47:15.166 --> 00:47:17.374
If you poison us, do we not die?

621
00:47:17.624 --> 00:47:20.332
And, if you wrong us,
shall we not revenge?"

622
00:47:28.332 --> 00:47:31.832
-Very appropriate.
-Yes. That's why I brought it.

623
00:47:31.999 --> 00:47:33.999
[sorrowful orchestral music playing]

624
00:47:40.749 --> 00:47:42.957
[child cries]

625
00:47:49.582 --> 00:47:52.416
Idiot. What's he think he's
going to do with the money?

626
00:47:54.291 --> 00:47:57.082
Hey boy, come here.

627
00:47:57.832 --> 00:47:59.082
[father] Come here.

628
00:48:00.957 --> 00:48:02.999
-[father] How much for a caramel?
-Twenty zlotys.

629
00:48:03.749 --> 00:48:06.749
What? For one caramel? What do you think
you're going to do with the money?

630
00:48:06.832 --> 00:48:08.124
Twenty zlotys.

631
00:48:10.624 --> 00:48:12.874
We've got 20 between us.

632
00:48:12.957 --> 00:48:14.874
I've got ten, I think.

633
00:48:18.332 --> 00:48:20.041
Five, ten, twenty.

634
00:48:32.666 --> 00:48:34.666
[young woman cries] Why did I do it?

635
00:48:57.291 --> 00:49:02.041
[young woman cries] Why did I do it?
Why did I do it? Why did I do it?

636
00:49:11.749 --> 00:49:17.291
[train brakes screeching]

637
00:49:28.499 --> 00:49:30.499
[German soldiers shouting in German]

638
00:49:31.666 --> 00:49:36.582
[German soldiers shouting in German]

639
00:49:38.374 --> 00:49:39.999
[German soldiers shouting in German]

640
00:49:43.957 --> 00:49:46.791
-Halina?
-What?

641
00:49:48.166 --> 00:49:51.707
-It's a funny time to say this, but...
-What?

642
00:49:53.124 --> 00:49:54.957
I wish I knew you better.

643
00:49:59.291 --> 00:50:00.707
Thank you.

644
00:50:01.457 --> 00:50:03.457
[German soldiers shouting in German]

645
00:50:06.374 --> 00:50:08.499
[German soldiers shouting in German]

646
00:50:12.041 --> 00:50:14.166
[German soldiers shouting in German]

647
00:50:17.707 --> 00:50:20.457
[Heller] Szpilman? Szpilman!

648
00:50:25.582 --> 00:50:28.499
Fuck off stupid! Go!

649
00:50:29.082 --> 00:50:31.499
Papa? Papa?

650
00:50:32.291 --> 00:50:35.957
Papa? Mama? Halina?

651
00:50:36.957 --> 00:50:38.999
Halina? Mama?

652
00:50:40.082 --> 00:50:44.332
What do you think you're doing Szpilman?
I've saved your life. Get out, just go! Go!

653
00:50:48.707 --> 00:50:49.916
[Heller] Don't run!

654
00:50:52.666 --> 00:50:57.166
Mama! Mama! Mama!

655
00:50:57.666 --> 00:50:58.957
[German soldier speaking in German]

656
00:51:03.082 --> 00:51:04.874
[German officers shout indistinctly]

657
00:51:16.791 --> 00:51:20.999
-Well, off they go to the melting pot.
-Ah! <i>Ja.</i>

658
00:51:22.999 --> 00:51:26.874
[German soldier speaking German]

659
00:51:32.791 --> 00:51:35.166
What are you doing? She's pregnant!

660
00:51:43.249 --> 00:51:45.249
[shouting, screaming]

661
00:52:06.957 --> 00:52:10.457
[train horn hoots loudly]

662
00:52:28.374 --> 00:52:30.166
[sobs uncontrollably]

663
00:52:49.874 --> 00:52:51.916
[sorrowful orchestral music]

664
00:53:41.249 --> 00:53:43.249
[flies buzzing]

665
00:54:02.666 --> 00:54:03.707
[Benek] Wladek?

666
00:54:21.582 --> 00:54:25.166
[sighs heavily] Why are you here, Wladek?

667
00:54:26.041 --> 00:54:28.749
It's like this, I, I...

668
00:54:30.416 --> 00:54:32.332
We...

669
00:54:34.624 --> 00:54:37.624
AII of them, all of them.

670
00:54:37.707 --> 00:54:39.166
AII of them.

671
00:54:41.082 --> 00:54:45.082
Perhaps they're lucky.
The quicker, the better.

672
00:54:45.166 --> 00:54:48.332
It's not finished yet.
We'll stay here for a couple of days,

673
00:54:48.582 --> 00:54:50.124
until things die down.

674
00:54:50.791 --> 00:54:53.374
I've bribed a policeman,
he'll come when it's over.

675
00:54:56.457 --> 00:54:58.166
[soldier speaking German]

676
00:54:58.874 --> 00:55:00.666
[soldier speaking German]

677
00:55:10.166 --> 00:55:11.374
[soldier speaking German]

678
00:55:14.416 --> 00:55:17.749
My God, I haven't been outside in,
it must be two years.

679
00:55:17.832 --> 00:55:19.666
Don't get overexcited.

680
00:55:21.041 --> 00:55:23.124
[indistinct chatter]

681
00:55:23.207 --> 00:55:25.207
[sorrowful orchestral music]

682
00:55:36.541 --> 00:55:39.916
It's gold. Very good price.

683
00:56:00.957 --> 00:56:01.999
Someone you know?

684
00:56:03.041 --> 00:56:04.791
A beauty. Who is she?

685
00:56:05.332 --> 00:56:09.207
She's a singer. I knew her well actually.
Her husband's an actor.

686
00:56:09.541 --> 00:56:12.124
They're good people.
I'd like to talk to her.

687
00:56:12.207 --> 00:56:15.082
Don't forget, Wladek.
They hang them for helping Jews.

688
00:56:42.999 --> 00:56:47.291
[speaking German]

689
00:56:52.374 --> 00:56:55.624
-[SS soldier] Stop!
-[soldier] Halt!

690
00:57:02.499 --> 00:57:04.249
[SS soldier speaking German]

691
00:57:09.499 --> 00:57:10.666
[speaking German]

692
00:57:19.374 --> 00:57:20.499
[speaking German]

693
00:57:20.666 --> 00:57:21.957
[SS soldier speaking German]

694
00:57:22.582 --> 00:57:23.791
[SS soldier speaking German]

695
00:57:26.416 --> 00:57:28.957
[SS soldier speaking German]

696
00:57:29.707 --> 00:57:30.749
[SS soldier speaking German]

697
00:57:35.457 --> 00:57:36.832
[SS soldier shouting in German]

698
00:57:37.666 --> 00:57:38.874
[SS soldier shouting in German]

699
00:58:08.082 --> 00:58:09.457
[soldier speaking German]

700
00:58:11.374 --> 00:58:13.499
[soldier speaking German]

701
00:58:40.582 --> 00:58:41.957
[man whistles]

702
00:58:46.249 --> 00:58:49.916
[soldier speaking German]

703
00:58:51.499 --> 00:58:52.916
[whistle blows]

704
00:58:53.957 --> 00:58:55.249
How long have you been here?

705
00:58:56.416 --> 00:58:57.707
Since last night.

706
00:58:59.541 --> 00:59:01.082
I was pleased to see you.

707
00:59:05.832 --> 00:59:07.957
They're going to start
the final resettlement now.

708
00:59:11.041 --> 00:59:12.582
We know what it means.

709
00:59:14.666 --> 00:59:18.249
We sent someone out.
Zygmunt, a good man.

710
00:59:20.832 --> 00:59:23.124
His orders were to follow
the trains out of Warsaw.

711
00:59:25.666 --> 00:59:26.957
He got to Sokolow.

712
00:59:28.041 --> 00:59:30.666
A local railway man told
him the tracks divided,

713
00:59:30.916 --> 00:59:32.916
one branch leading to Treblinka.

714
00:59:34.582 --> 00:59:38.541
He said everyday freight trains
carrying people from Warsaw...

715
00:59:38.624 --> 00:59:41.707
branched off to Treblinka
and returned empty.

716
00:59:43.041 --> 00:59:45.166
No transports of food
are ever seen on that line.

717
00:59:46.624 --> 00:59:50.166
And civilians are forbidden
to approach the Treblinka station.

718
00:59:54.374 --> 00:59:55.874
They're exterminating us.

719
01:00:00.541 --> 01:00:02.166
It won't take them long.

720
01:00:04.582 --> 01:00:07.582
We're 60 thousand left,
out of half a million.

721
01:00:08.957 --> 01:00:10.499
Mostly young people.

722
01:00:12.791 --> 01:00:14.624
And this time we're going to fight.

723
01:00:17.624 --> 01:00:18.999
We're in good shape.

724
01:00:20.582 --> 01:00:23.832
Organized. We're prepared.

725
01:00:24.707 --> 01:00:26.416
If you need help, I...

726
01:00:29.582 --> 01:00:30.916
[whistle blows]
[dog barks]

727
01:00:46.832 --> 01:00:49.624
[Zig-Zag] You! Come here!

728
01:00:51.124 --> 01:00:51.999
Shit!

729
01:01:01.166 --> 01:01:02.999
[Wladek] I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

730
01:01:03.541 --> 01:01:05.957
[Wladek]
I, I don't know what I was thinking.

731
01:01:16.249 --> 01:01:19.332
[speaking German]

732
01:01:19.832 --> 01:01:21.874
[Wladek groans]

733
01:01:35.457 --> 01:01:37.207
[in German] Get him away from here.

734
01:01:51.457 --> 01:01:52.666
[groans]

735
01:01:53.582 --> 01:01:56.707
I hope you play the piano better
than you carry bricks.

736
01:01:59.207 --> 01:02:01.541
He won't last long
if he goes on like this.

737
01:02:01.916 --> 01:02:04.541
I’ll see if I can get him
something better.

738
01:02:24.791 --> 01:02:25.874
[whistle blows]

739
01:02:27.374 --> 01:02:28.541
Trouble.

740
01:02:29.457 --> 01:02:32.041
[German soldier # 1 in German]
Assemble! Fall in!

741
01:02:32.207 --> 01:02:34.999
[German soldier # 2]
Round up! Only the Jews.

742
01:02:35.374 --> 01:02:38.832
[German soldier # 2] Poles go on working.
Only the Jews!

743
01:02:45.999 --> 01:02:48.582
I have good news for you.

744
01:02:49.166 --> 01:02:54.249
There are rumors going around
that we like to, uh...

745
01:02:54.332 --> 01:02:57.249
<i>umsiedeln.</i>.. Resettle you.

746
01:02:59.457 --> 01:03:04.166
I promise you that now
and in the future...

747
01:03:04.666 --> 01:03:07.166
nothing else is planned.

748
01:03:08.957 --> 01:03:15.666
<i>Ja?</i> For this reason, we put
information posters on the wall.

749
01:03:16.957 --> 01:03:20.332
To show you our goodwill...

750
01:03:20.416 --> 01:03:24.499
you should vote one of you
to be allowed...

751
01:03:24.582 --> 01:03:27.374
to go in town daily...

752
01:03:28.041 --> 01:03:34.082
and bring three kilos
of <i>Kartoffeln</i> potatoes, j*

753
01:03:34.416 --> 01:03:38.541
And one loaf of bread
for each of your workers.

754
01:03:39.082 --> 01:03:44.332
So, why should we do something else
like this if we would resettle you?

755
01:03:45.624 --> 01:03:50.999
You can make good business
out of the things you don't eat.

756
01:03:52.457 --> 01:03:58.082
Isn't that something that you Jews
are good in? Make money?

757
01:04:02.124 --> 01:04:03.207
[in German] Carry on.

758
01:04:04.707 --> 01:04:07.249
[German soldier speaking German]

759
01:04:19.457 --> 01:04:23.541
That one, with the string.
The others, tied by wire.

760
01:04:34.457 --> 01:04:36.541
[German soldier speaking German]

761
01:04:39.041 --> 01:04:41.207
[German soldier speaking German]

762
01:04:47.541 --> 01:04:49.707
[German soldier speaking German]

763
01:04:53.916 --> 01:04:55.916
[German soldier speaking German]

764
01:05:06.957 --> 01:05:08.999
[German soldier speaking German]

765
01:05:10.707 --> 01:05:12.707
[dog barks]
[German soldier speaking German]

766
01:05:32.374 --> 01:05:33.291
[Majorek] Now!

767
01:05:41.791 --> 01:05:43.041
[man coughs]

768
01:06:11.041 --> 01:06:12.082
Majorek.

769
01:06:14.749 --> 01:06:16.332
I have a favor to ask.

770
01:06:18.041 --> 01:06:19.457
I want to get out of here.

771
01:06:23.374 --> 01:06:27.957
It's easy to get out. It's how you
survive on the other side that's hard.

772
01:06:28.041 --> 01:06:29.041
I know.

773
01:06:30.916 --> 01:06:35.166
Last summer, I worked for a day
in the Zelazna Brama Square.

774
01:06:35.249 --> 01:06:37.874
I saw someone I knew,
she's an old friend.

775
01:06:38.957 --> 01:06:41.124
A singer, her husband's an actor.

776
01:06:41.207 --> 01:06:42.624
[man coughs]

777
01:06:43.999 --> 01:06:48.207
I filled their names down
and their address, if they're still there.

778
01:06:48.291 --> 01:06:52.457
Janina Godlewska and Andrzej Bogucki.
They're good people.

779
01:06:54.166 --> 01:06:55.957
Would you try to make contact?

780
01:06:58.249 --> 01:06:59.249
You go to town every day.

781
01:06:59.332 --> 01:07:03.332
Would you just ask them, ask them
if they'd help me get out of here?

782
01:07:19.041 --> 01:07:20.166
[man coughs]

783
01:07:34.999 --> 01:07:36.249
[door opens]

784
01:07:36.999 --> 01:07:38.874
[in German] Got a plaster?

785
01:07:48.832 --> 01:07:51.041
[in German] What are you up to?

786
01:07:53.749 --> 01:07:55.666
What's in that?

787
01:07:56.499 --> 01:07:59.666
[in German] We're allowed to take food
into the ghetto.

788
01:08:00.874 --> 01:08:02.957
[in German]
Three kilos of potato and bread.

789
01:08:03.749 --> 01:08:04.999
[in German] Open it.

790
01:08:09.082 --> 01:08:11.124
[in German]
It's only potatoes and bread.

791
01:08:11.207 --> 01:08:14.416
[in German] You're lying. I can smell it.

792
01:08:15.874 --> 01:08:17.332
[in German] Open it.

793
01:08:46.082 --> 01:08:47.416
[in German] Potatoes!

794
01:08:51.749 --> 01:08:54.374
[in German] You Jews are all the same.

795
01:08:55.707 --> 01:08:58.291
[in German]
Give a Jew your little finger...

796
01:08:58.832 --> 01:09:00.999
and he takes the whole hand.

797
01:09:15.291 --> 01:09:19.332
[in German] Lie to me again,
I’ll shoot you... personally.

798
01:09:43.416 --> 01:09:44.999
[Majorek] I tried your friends.

799
01:09:45.916 --> 01:09:48.749
-They don't live there anymore.
-Did you make contact?

800
01:09:50.166 --> 01:09:52.374
-Be ready to leave.
-When?

801
01:09:52.457 --> 01:09:54.124
-Soon.
-[Zig-Zag] Halt!

802
01:09:55.249 --> 01:09:57.916
-[soldier speaking German]
-[Wladek] Oh, shit! Shit!

803
01:09:57.999 --> 01:10:00.332
[soldier speaking German]

804
01:10:00.416 --> 01:10:04.416
[Zig-Zag speaking German
as he whips the Jews]

805
01:10:10.916 --> 01:10:14.207
[in German]
I’ll teach you discipline, you dirty pigs!

806
01:10:19.291 --> 01:10:20.999
[in German] Know why we're beating you?

807
01:10:21.374 --> 01:10:22.249
[in German] No.

808
01:10:22.416 --> 01:10:24.416
[in German]
Know why we beat you?

809
01:10:25.082 --> 01:10:28.582
-[in German] Why?
-[in German] To celebrate New Year's Eve.

810
01:10:28.666 --> 01:10:29.582
[laughs]

811
01:10:31.916 --> 01:10:34.124
No, quick march! March!

812
01:10:34.666 --> 01:10:36.791
[Zig-Zag in German] March and sing!

813
01:10:37.749 --> 01:10:39.124
[Zig-Zag in German]
Sing something cheerful!

814
01:10:40.166 --> 01:10:42.249
[Zig-Zag in German]
Sing it loud and clear!

815
01:10:42.332 --> 01:10:43.332
[laughs]

816
01:10:43.666 --> 01:10:47.749
[Column sings] ♪ <i>Hey ranks unite
and follow the white eagle ♪</i>

817
01:10:47.832 --> 01:10:51.999
[all sing] <i>♪ Stand up and fight
our mortal enemies ♪</i>

818
01:10:52.166 --> 01:10:56.249
<i>♪ Riflemen, hey
Let's give them fire and brimstone ♪</i>

819
01:10:56.332 --> 01:11:00.207
<i>♪ We'll blow away the yoke of slavery ♪</i>

820
01:11:00.374 --> 01:11:04.207
<i>♪ Punish and rout
the rapists of our nation ♪</i>

821
01:11:04.291 --> 01:11:08.499
<i>♪ We'll smash the knout
to save our dignity ♪</i>

822
01:11:08.666 --> 01:11:10.624
[soldiers speaking German]

823
01:11:22.749 --> 01:11:25.791
[soldier speaking German]
[dog barks]

824
01:11:30.666 --> 01:11:32.707
[indistinct chatter]

825
01:11:42.041 --> 01:11:43.332
[speaking German]

826
01:12:47.957 --> 01:12:49.916
[crying]

827
01:12:58.832 --> 01:13:00.166
I'm sorry.

828
01:13:00.249 --> 01:13:03.041
I'm dirty. I'm so filthy.
[sniffs]

829
01:13:28.624 --> 01:13:30.832
We haven't much time. Come on.

830
01:13:36.874 --> 01:13:38.291
[knock on bathroom door]
[door opens]

831
01:13:39.207 --> 01:13:40.416
We must hurry.

832
01:13:41.249 --> 01:13:42.624
Here. See if these fit.

833
01:13:43.624 --> 01:13:45.291
[Bogucki]
We're going to have to keep moving you.

834
01:13:45.457 --> 01:13:47.957
The Germans are hunting
down indiscriminately now.

835
01:13:48.041 --> 01:13:51.249
Jews, non-Jews, anybody, everybody.

836
01:13:51.332 --> 01:13:55.332
And Wladek, you'd better shave.
Use my razor on the shelf.

837
01:14:10.249 --> 01:14:12.291
You’ll be looked after
by Marek Gebczynski.

838
01:14:13.374 --> 01:14:14.957
He's on the other side of town.

839
01:14:15.541 --> 01:14:18.166
You stay there tonight,
then we’ll find you somewhere else.

840
01:14:20.207 --> 01:14:23.624
-I’ll bring you food.
-Alright, let's go.

841
01:14:28.332 --> 01:14:30.332
[melancholic orchestral music]

842
01:15:03.499 --> 01:15:05.707
I’ll show you where
you're going to sleep.

843
01:15:36.999 --> 01:15:39.707
You have to stay here
until tomorrow afternoon.

844
01:15:40.249 --> 01:15:44.791
We have a flat for you near
the ghetto wall. But it's safe.

845
01:15:52.374 --> 01:15:54.416
It's not going to be very comfortable.

846
01:15:55.416 --> 01:15:56.332
I’ll be fine.

847
01:16:06.957 --> 01:16:08.166
Thank you.

848
01:16:22.374 --> 01:16:23.999
[tram bell rings]

849
01:16:24.999 --> 01:16:27.374
I’ll take it. Here. Give it to me.

850
01:16:28.374 --> 01:16:31.416
Go as near to the front as possible,
to the German section.

851
01:16:50.457 --> 01:16:51.749
DO NOT PASS

852
01:16:57.374 --> 01:16:59.332
[tram bell rings]

853
01:17:23.499 --> 01:17:25.291
[Gebczynski]
I'm going to draw the curtains now.

854
01:17:31.541 --> 01:17:34.541
But you leave them open
during the daytime. Don't forget.

855
01:17:38.249 --> 01:17:41.041
Must feel better on
this side of the wall, huh?

856
01:17:41.791 --> 01:17:42.791
Yes.

857
01:17:44.541 --> 01:17:47.749
But sometimes I'm still not sure
which side of the wall I'm on.

858
01:17:51.041 --> 01:17:53.957
[Gebczynski] Some bread, potatoes, onions.

859
01:17:54.791 --> 01:17:58.332
I’ll come again. And Janina Bogucki
will visit twice a week.

860
01:17:58.416 --> 01:18:00.499
Bring more food, see how you are.

861
01:18:01.291 --> 01:18:02.374
Thank you.

862
01:18:04.582 --> 01:18:09.124
Oh, this is very important.
In case of emergency...

863
01:18:09.207 --> 01:18:12.707
I mean emergency,
go to this address.

864
01:18:18.832 --> 01:18:20.832
[Gebczynski locks the door]

865
01:18:30.124 --> 01:18:32.124
[groans, sighs heavily]

866
01:18:45.999 --> 01:18:47.457
[groans]

867
01:18:49.832 --> 01:18:51.832
[groans, sighs]

868
01:18:53.166 --> 01:18:54.874
[exhales heavily]

869
01:18:55.874 --> 01:18:58.416
[woman playing kitten's voice next door]
<i>Puppy dog, what do you mean you forgot?</i>

870
01:18:58.499 --> 01:18:59.916
[man playing puppy dog's voice]
<i>What do you think I mean, Kitten?</i>

871
01:18:59.999 --> 01:19:01.582
<i>I forgot, that’s what I mean.</i>

872
01:19:01.666 --> 01:19:04.166
[Kitten's voice]
<i>You know what, you treat me like dirt.</i>

873
01:19:04.249 --> 01:19:07.124
[Puppy dog's voice] <i>I treat you
like dirt because you are dirt.</i>

874
01:19:07.291 --> 01:19:09.791
-[Kitten's voice] <i>Pig! Pig!</i>
-[Puppy dog's voice] <i>Bitch!</i>

875
01:19:10.166 --> 01:19:12.749
-[Kitten's voice] <i>Dirty pig!</i>
-[Puppy dog's voice] <i>You are a dirty pig!</i>

876
01:19:12.832 --> 01:19:14.832
[Kitten's voice]
<i>Takes one to know one. Pig.</i>

877
01:19:14.916 --> 01:19:19.541
[playing simple piano tune]

878
01:19:19.624 --> 01:19:22.166
[Puppy dog's voice]
<i>Hmm. You Play like an angel, Kitten.</i>

879
01:19:22.249 --> 01:19:23.874
[Kitten's voice] <i>I’ll play like an angel,
why don't you listen?</i>

880
01:19:23.957 --> 01:19:24.749
[Wladek chuckles]

881
01:19:24.832 --> 01:19:26.207
[Puppy dog's voice]
<i>I was listening, Kitten.</i>

882
01:19:26.291 --> 01:19:29.749
[Kitten's voice] <i>Liar!
You fell asleep, Pig!</i>

883
01:19:29.832 --> 01:19:31.832
[piano playing continues]

884
01:19:32.832 --> 01:19:34.249
[bomb explodes nearby]

885
01:19:39.582 --> 01:19:41.332
[gunshots, rapid gunfire]

886
01:19:51.082 --> 01:19:52.082
[gunshot]

887
01:19:52.166 --> 01:19:54.791
[German soldier shouts in German]

888
01:19:55.332 --> 01:19:57.832
[gunshot, rapid gunfire]

889
01:19:58.332 --> 01:20:00.582
[German soldier shouts in German]

890
01:20:02.249 --> 01:20:03.457
[German soldier shouts in German]

891
01:20:03.624 --> 01:20:05.416
[glass shatters]
[gunshot]

892
01:20:15.291 --> 01:20:18.457
[German soldier shouts in German]

893
01:20:18.624 --> 01:20:20.957
[gunshots, rapid fire continues]

894
01:20:22.291 --> 01:20:24.124
[German soldier shouts in German]

895
01:20:32.291 --> 01:20:33.582
[rapid gunfire]

896
01:20:36.416 --> 01:20:37.499
[rapid gunfire]

897
01:20:45.874 --> 01:20:47.416
[German soldier shouts in German]

898
01:20:51.082 --> 01:20:52.624
[German soldier shouts in German]

899
01:20:52.791 --> 01:20:54.707
[gunshots, rapid fire continues]

900
01:21:12.041 --> 01:21:14.457
[sorrowful orchestral music]

901
01:21:25.874 --> 01:21:27.499
[rapid gunfire continues]

902
01:21:27.666 --> 01:21:30.041
[sorrowful orchestral music continues]

903
01:21:31.832 --> 01:21:33.832
[German soldiers cheering]

904
01:21:37.999 --> 01:21:41.999
[German soldiers cheering]

905
01:21:42.166 --> 01:21:44.874
[sorrowful orchestral music continues]

906
01:21:50.207 --> 01:21:52.416
[German soldier shouts in German]

907
01:21:52.832 --> 01:21:55.749
[speaking German]

908
01:21:57.124 --> 01:21:57.999
[speaking German]

909
01:21:58.624 --> 01:22:00.874
[sorrowful orchestral music continues]

910
01:22:05.624 --> 01:22:07.082
[speaking German]

911
01:22:07.249 --> 01:22:09.291
[soldier speaking German]

912
01:22:09.374 --> 01:22:11.666
[sorrowful orchestral music continues]

913
01:22:15.832 --> 01:22:16.916
[soldier shouts command in German]

914
01:22:42.291 --> 01:22:43.249
Thank you.

915
01:22:47.499 --> 01:22:50.791
-I wanted to come earlier, but...
-No, no, no, thank you.

916
01:22:51.041 --> 01:22:53.041
[pigeon flies away]

917
01:22:54.749 --> 01:22:57.416
[Janina] No-one thought
they'd hold out so long.

918
01:22:58.707 --> 01:23:01.416
I never should have come out. I should've
stayed there and fought with them.

919
01:23:01.499 --> 01:23:04.957
Wladek, stop that. It's over now.

920
01:23:05.041 --> 01:23:07.082
Just be proud it happened.

921
01:23:08.207 --> 01:23:11.707
-My God, did they put up a fight!
-Yes.

922
01:23:13.791 --> 01:23:16.374
-So did the Germans.
-They're in shock!

923
01:23:16.791 --> 01:23:22.166
They didn't expect it.
Nobody expected it. Jews fighting back?

924
01:23:22.707 --> 01:23:26.666
-Who would have thought?
-What good did it do?

925
01:23:27.582 --> 01:23:29.082
What good?

926
01:23:29.957 --> 01:23:31.624
Wladek, I'm surprised at you.

927
01:23:32.541 --> 01:23:34.999
They died with dignity,
that's what good it did.

928
01:23:36.166 --> 01:23:37.207
And you know something else?

929
01:23:38.207 --> 01:23:41.874
Now the Poles will rise. We're ready.

930
01:23:42.457 --> 01:23:45.541
We’ll fight too. You’ll see.

931
01:23:52.874 --> 01:23:53.957
[door opens]

932
01:24:00.166 --> 01:24:03.166
Get your things together.
You have to leave.

933
01:24:03.249 --> 01:24:05.624
P[Wladek] What? What's happened?

934
01:24:08.082 --> 01:24:10.541
-[Gebczynski] I'm on the run.
-What's happened?

935
01:24:10.624 --> 01:24:14.624
The Gestapo found our weapons.
They've arrested Janina and Andrzej.

936
01:24:15.624 --> 01:24:19.749
They're bound to find out about this
place too. You must get away at once.

937
01:24:19.916 --> 01:24:21.124
Where do you want me to go?

938
01:24:22.207 --> 01:24:24.999
Look at me, I'm not leaving.

939
01:24:26.791 --> 01:24:29.541
-Can I take my chances here?
-That's your decision.

940
01:24:30.374 --> 01:24:33.291
But when they storm the flat,
throw yourself out the window,

941
01:24:33.374 --> 01:24:34.832
don't let them get you alive.

942
01:24:35.291 --> 01:24:37.749
I have poison on me.
They won't get me alive either.

