960
01:26:34.749 --> 01:26:37.332
[piano playing next door]
[clock ticking]

961
01:27:38.749 --> 01:27:40.749
[piano playing stops]

962
01:27:48.957 --> 01:27:50.791
[knock on front door]

963
01:27:52.416 --> 01:27:53.999
[knock on front door]

964
01:27:54.749 --> 01:27:56.124
[woman] Open up!

965
01:27:57.207 --> 01:27:59.707
[knock on front door]

966
01:27:59.791 --> 01:28:02.332
[woman shouts] Open this door
at once or we’ll call the police!

967
01:28:31.707 --> 01:28:35.791
Are you from this flat?
You're not registered.

968
01:28:35.957 --> 01:28:36.957
It belongs to a friend of mine.

969
01:28:37.041 --> 01:28:39.457
I just came to visit,
but I must have just missed him.

970
01:28:39.541 --> 01:28:41.166
Have you got your identity card?

971
01:28:41.332 --> 01:28:42.291
What?

972
01:28:42.624 --> 01:28:44.582
-Let me see your identity card.
-Yes, of course.

973
01:28:45.666 --> 01:28:46.707
[door opens]

974
01:28:47.957 --> 01:28:50.624
-I want to see your identity card!
-What's happening?

975
01:28:50.707 --> 01:28:52.999
He's a Jew! A Jew!

976
01:28:53.582 --> 01:28:55.457
Stop the Jew!

977
01:28:56.916 --> 01:28:59.332
Don't let him out! Stop him!

978
01:28:59.499 --> 01:29:01.541
[dramatic orchestral music]

979
01:30:12.749 --> 01:30:16.457
-[Dorota] Yes?
-Mr. Gebczynski sent me.

980
01:30:23.124 --> 01:30:27.166
-Wladyslaw Szpilman.
-Dorota.

981
01:30:28.457 --> 01:30:29.874
Come in.

982
01:30:37.374 --> 01:30:39.541
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

983
01:30:39.624 --> 01:30:42.791
I was given this address
and I'm looking for a Mr. Dzikiewicz.

984
01:30:42.874 --> 01:30:45.832
Michal Dzikiewicz, he's my husband.

985
01:30:46.791 --> 01:30:47.999
Come in.

986
01:30:56.457 --> 01:30:57.582
Sit.

987
01:31:01.416 --> 01:31:02.791
I need help.

988
01:31:05.582 --> 01:31:06.957
He’ll be back before curfew.

989
01:31:07.457 --> 01:31:10.249
I've... I've been in hiding.

990
01:31:10.916 --> 01:31:12.416
[sniffs, exhales]

991
01:31:12.499 --> 01:31:15.416
-I need somewhere to stay.
-He’ll be here soon.

992
01:31:18.166 --> 01:31:21.249
-How long have you been married?
-Just over a year.

993
01:31:24.082 --> 01:31:26.166
And... how's Jurek?

994
01:31:26.916 --> 01:31:28.082
Dead.

995
01:31:28.874 --> 01:31:30.082
Oh...

996
01:31:35.249 --> 01:31:38.582
-And when, when is your baby due?
-Christmas.

997
01:31:39.707 --> 01:31:41.707
This is not a good time to have children,

998
01:31:41.791 --> 01:31:43.499
-[door opens, closes]
-but then...

999
01:31:45.749 --> 01:31:49.332
This is my husband. Wladyslaw Szpilman.

1000
01:31:49.416 --> 01:31:53.582
-Marek Gebczynski sent him.
-Oh, yes, I remember.

1001
01:31:56.249 --> 01:31:58.916
Mr. Gebczynski said to contact you
only in case of emergency.

1002
01:31:58.999 --> 01:31:59.999
Don't worry now.

1003
01:32:10.041 --> 01:32:13.166
We can't move you tonight.
You’ll sleep on the sofa.

1004
01:32:18.082 --> 01:32:19.874
Oh! Excuse me.

1005
01:32:24.457 --> 01:32:26.791
I'm sorry, could I,
could I have a piece of bread?

1006
01:32:27.707 --> 01:32:29.624
Yes, of course. We’ll eat.

1007
01:32:31.124 --> 01:32:33.916
Sit. Please, sit.

1008
01:32:34.957 --> 01:32:36.332
Thank you.

1009
01:32:41.791 --> 01:32:43.291
[sighs heavily]

1010
01:32:43.874 --> 01:32:45.916
[cello playing nearby]

1011
01:33:57.541 --> 01:33:59.124
[door clicks open, squeaks]

1012
01:34:40.916 --> 01:34:43.041
[tram bells rings]

1013
01:34:45.041 --> 01:34:46.832
[Michal] You're in a very German area.

1014
01:34:48.291 --> 01:34:51.791
The building opposite is a hospital
taking in wounded from the Russian front.

1015
01:34:54.457 --> 01:34:56.582
And next door is the Schutzpolizei.

1016
01:34:59.207 --> 01:35:00.707
[Michal] Safest place to be.

1017
01:35:01.707 --> 01:35:03.666
Right in the heart of the lion's den.

1018
01:35:09.707 --> 01:35:11.082
I’ll be locking you in.

1019
01:35:12.082 --> 01:35:15.582
No-one knows you're here,
so keep as quiet as possible.

1020
01:35:38.499 --> 01:35:40.249
[tram bell rings]

1021
01:36:07.457 --> 01:36:09.457
[passionate orchestral music]

1022
01:36:32.791 --> 01:36:34.749
[piano joins the orchestra]

1023
01:37:01.624 --> 01:37:03.749
[front door lock clicks open]

1024
01:37:25.332 --> 01:37:26.207
AII well?

1025
01:37:28.207 --> 01:37:29.082
Thank you.

1026
01:37:34.832 --> 01:37:37.666
This is Antek Szalas.
He’ll be looking after you.

1027
01:37:38.791 --> 01:37:39.916
-How do you do?
-How do you do?

1028
01:37:40.624 --> 01:37:41.791
Thank you.

1029
01:37:42.499 --> 01:37:47.291
I've given him a second key. He’ll
bring you food, see that you're alright.

1030
01:37:48.166 --> 01:37:50.291
He's with the underground,
he's a good man.

1031
01:37:54.832 --> 01:37:59.124
-You don't remember me Mr. Szpilman?
-I don't think so.

1032
01:37:59.207 --> 01:38:02.624
Warsaw Radio. I was a technician.

1033
01:38:03.291 --> 01:38:05.332
[Szalas] I saw you almost every day.

1034
01:38:05.749 --> 01:38:06.832
[Szalas pours a drink]

1035
01:38:07.332 --> 01:38:10.041
-I'm sorry, I don't remember, I...
-It doesn't matter.

1036
01:38:12.749 --> 01:38:15.874
You've nothing to worry about.
I’ll visit often.

1037
01:38:17.291 --> 01:38:20.041
You’ll be pleased to hear that
the Allies are bombing Germany...

1038
01:38:20.124 --> 01:38:22.124
night after night, after night.

1039
01:38:22.499 --> 01:38:25.124
Cologne, Hamburg, Berlin.

1040
01:38:25.207 --> 01:38:28.624
And the Russians are really giving
them hell. It's the beginning of the end.

1041
01:38:28.707 --> 01:38:29.916
Oh, let's hope so.

1042
01:38:31.082 --> 01:38:33.207
[siren wails]

1043
01:38:41.124 --> 01:38:42.541
[man speaking German]

1044
01:38:43.541 --> 01:38:45.749
[man speaking German]

1045
01:38:46.666 --> 01:38:49.624
[man speaking German]

1046
01:38:53.166 --> 01:38:55.166
[sorrowful orchestral music]

1047
01:39:00.166 --> 01:39:02.166
[key jangles in front door]

1048
01:39:16.624 --> 01:39:17.916
Still alive then?

1049
01:39:22.749 --> 01:39:26.749
Here. Sausage, bread.

1050
01:39:26.832 --> 01:39:28.457
You still got that vodka?

1051
01:39:43.332 --> 01:39:46.874
-How long is this meant to last?
-Not long now.

1052
01:39:48.207 --> 01:39:50.416
I think, I think I've got jaundice.

1053
01:39:51.457 --> 01:39:55.207
Don't worry about that.
It just makes you look funny.

1054
01:39:56.541 --> 01:39:59.874
My grandfather was jilted by
his girlfriend when he got jaundice.

1055
01:40:00.707 --> 01:40:01.582
Drink up.

1056
01:40:01.666 --> 01:40:03.332
[siren wails in background]

1057
01:40:03.416 --> 01:40:06.666
Why didn't you come sooner?
It's been over two weeks.

1058
01:40:06.749 --> 01:40:07.999
-I got--
-Problems.

1059
01:40:08.749 --> 01:40:10.916
-Money.
-[car door slams]

1060
01:40:11.332 --> 01:40:13.332
I've got to raise money to buy the food.

1061
01:40:14.041 --> 01:40:17.082
I need things to sell,
it's not easy.

1062
01:40:17.166 --> 01:40:19.166
[man speaking German outside]

1063
01:40:21.749 --> 01:40:23.916
[Wladek] Here. Sell this.

1064
01:40:26.749 --> 01:40:28.791
Food's more important than time.

1065
01:40:29.332 --> 01:40:31.457
[car engine revs]

1066
01:40:31.541 --> 01:40:33.541
[siren wails]

1067
01:40:34.207 --> 01:40:37.416
Oh, yes. I meant to tell you!
The Allies have landed in France.

1068
01:40:37.499 --> 01:40:39.374
Russians will be here soon.

1069
01:40:40.249 --> 01:40:42.332
They’ll beat the shit
out of the Germans...

1070
01:40:44.082 --> 01:40:45.499
any day now.

1071
01:40:58.666 --> 01:41:00.666
[locks door]

1072
01:41:02.374 --> 01:41:03.374
[Wladek sighs]

1073
01:41:03.457 --> 01:41:05.291
[forlorn orchestral music]

1074
01:41:29.916 --> 01:41:30.957
Wladek?

1075
01:41:36.457 --> 01:41:37.457
Wladek?

1076
01:41:41.207 --> 01:41:44.249
I knew it. I knew this would happen.

1077
01:41:44.749 --> 01:41:46.374
[Wladek whimpers]

1078
01:41:46.541 --> 01:41:48.957
-I’ll get a doctor.
-You can't. It's too dangerous.

1079
01:41:49.041 --> 01:41:51.957
-I’ll get Dr. Luczak. We can trust him.
-Dorota. Don't be ridiculous,

1080
01:41:52.041 --> 01:41:52.957
he's a pediatrician.

1081
01:41:53.041 --> 01:41:55.041
-He's still a doctor.
-No.

1082
01:41:55.791 --> 01:41:58.249
You stay. I’ll go.

1083
01:42:12.291 --> 01:42:13.541
[tram bell rings]

1084
01:42:26.416 --> 01:42:27.874
[Wladek whimpers]

1085
01:42:31.707 --> 01:42:33.582
We came to say goodbye.

1086
01:42:34.791 --> 01:42:37.749
We're going to stay
with my mother in Otwocks.

1087
01:42:37.999 --> 01:42:40.041
The baby's already there. It's safer.

1088
01:42:41.457 --> 01:42:44.457
There's talk that the uprising
will begin any day now.

1089
01:42:44.541 --> 01:42:46.374
[Wladek whimpers]

1090
01:42:46.832 --> 01:42:49.374
That man Szalas should be shot.

1091
01:42:50.749 --> 01:42:54.332
He's been collecting money
on your behalf all over Warsaw.

1092
01:42:54.874 --> 01:42:55.749
[Wladek moans]

1093
01:42:55.832 --> 01:43:00.541
Apparently people gave generously,
so he collected a tidy sum.

1094
01:43:00.707 --> 01:43:02.999
[Wladek coughs]

1095
01:43:04.707 --> 01:43:06.207
My God.

1096
01:43:11.082 --> 01:43:14.999
The liver the size of a football.
Acute inflammation of the gall bladder...

1097
01:43:16.707 --> 01:43:17.957
but he’ll live.

1098
01:43:21.624 --> 01:43:25.124
I’ll try to get him some levulose,
but it's not easy.

1099
01:43:25.999 --> 01:43:29.291
-Can you visit him again?
-Who knows.

1100
01:43:29.832 --> 01:43:33.832
-Doctor, thank you.
-Don't speak, rest.

1101
01:43:37.166 --> 01:43:38.791
Thank you so much for coming.

1102
01:43:41.874 --> 01:43:43.249
We've brought you some food.

1103
01:43:43.832 --> 01:43:46.999
I’ll prepare something now for you,
then we must go.

