What are you doing?

1192
02:02:28.332 --> 02:02:31.082
[in German] I, I was...

1193
02:02:31.707 --> 02:02:34.207
trying to open this can.

1194
02:02:35.499 --> 02:02:37.082
[in German] Do you live here?

1195
02:02:40.582 --> 02:02:42.666
[in German] Do you work here?

1196
02:02:42.749 --> 02:02:44.041
[Wladek in German] No.

1197
02:02:48.082 --> 02:02:49.666
[in German] What do you do?

1198
02:02:53.624 --> 02:02:54.791
[in German] I am...

1199
02:02:57.041 --> 02:02:59.249
I was a pianist.

1200
02:03:02.124 --> 02:03:03.457
Pianist?

1201
02:03:07.541 --> 02:03:12.041
[inhales and exhales deeply]

1202
02:03:13.541 --> 02:03:14.624
[scoffs]

1203
02:03:23.041 --> 02:03:24.416
[in German] Come on.

1204
02:03:26.541 --> 02:03:28.541
[metal clangs]

1205
02:03:50.166 --> 02:03:51.666
[in German] PIay something.

1206
02:04:46.582 --> 02:04:48.582
[playing Chopin]

1207
02:05:22.416 --> 02:05:25.957
[Wladek continues playing Chopin]

1208
02:07:10.582 --> 02:07:13.832
[Wladek continues playing Chopin]

1209
02:07:59.082 --> 02:08:01.124
[Wladek continues playing Chopin]

1210
02:09:11.249 --> 02:09:12.916
[in German] Are you hiding here?

1211
02:09:18.957 --> 02:09:20.082
[in German] Jew?

1212
02:09:23.332 --> 02:09:24.666
[in German] Where are you hiding?

1213
02:09:26.666 --> 02:09:27.666
[rapid gunfire nearby]

1214
02:09:27.749 --> 02:09:28.666
[in German] In the attic.

1215
02:09:31.249 --> 02:09:32.499
[rapid gunfire nearby]

1216
02:09:32.582 --> 02:09:33.666
[in German] Show me.

1217
02:09:58.291 --> 02:09:59.582
[in German] Got any food?

1218
02:10:34.916 --> 02:10:36.832
[sobbing]

1219
02:10:41.291 --> 02:10:43.207
[indistinct chatter in German]

1220
02:10:46.791 --> 02:10:53.124
[officer speaking German]

1221
02:10:55.291 --> 02:10:59.291
[typewriter keys tapping, telephone rings]

1222
02:10:59.374 --> 02:11:00.541
[German Officer speaking German]

1223
02:11:02.666 --> 02:11:05.416
-[German Captain speaking German]
-[German Officers speaking German]

1224
02:11:06.457 --> 02:11:08.957
[typewriter keys tapping]
[indistinct chatting in German]

1225
02:11:55.582 --> 02:11:57.457
[telephone rings]
[typewriter keys tapping]

1226
02:12:02.791 --> 02:12:04.791
[explosion, gunfire nearby]

1227
02:12:11.166 --> 02:12:12.541
[in German] Jew!

1228
02:12:12.624 --> 02:12:14.499
[explosion, gunfire nearby]

1229
02:12:26.041 --> 02:12:27.166
[explosion, gunfire nearby]

1230
02:12:27.249 --> 02:12:28.624
Excuse me. Please.

1231
02:12:29.207 --> 02:12:31.374
[in German] What's all that gunfire?

1232
02:12:32.082 --> 02:12:34.207
[in German] Russians. Across the river.

1233
02:12:36.124 --> 02:12:39.291
[in German]
All you have to do is wait a few weeks.

1234
02:12:41.624 --> 02:12:42.582
[door closes]

1235
02:13:08.416 --> 02:13:10.874
[groans in delight]

1236
02:13:10.957 --> 02:13:12.666
[explosion, gunfire nearby]

1237
02:13:18.666 --> 02:13:21.332
[explosion, gunfire nearby]

1238
02:13:29.749 --> 02:13:31.749
[explosion, gunfire nearby]

1239
02:13:34.957 --> 02:13:37.207
[indistinct chatter in German]

1240
02:14:10.832 --> 02:14:13.707
-[Wladek in German] What's happening?
-[in German] We're leaving.

1241
02:14:16.541 --> 02:14:19.624
-[in German] Are the Russians here?
-[in German] Not yet.

1242
02:14:22.791 --> 02:14:26.707
[in German]
I... I don't know how to thank you.

1243
02:14:28.166 --> 02:14:29.957
[in German] Thank God, not me.

1244
02:14:30.791 --> 02:14:36.374
[in German] He wants us to survive.
Well, that's what we have to believe.

1245
02:14:46.166 --> 02:14:48.666
[in German] Here. Take it.

1246
02:14:50.582 --> 02:14:53.124
-[in German] And you?
-[in German] I've got another...

1247
02:14:53.207 --> 02:14:54.832
[in German] a warmer one.

1248
02:14:59.541 --> 02:15:01.999
[in German]
What’ll you do when it's all over?

1249
02:15:04.666 --> 02:15:09.166
[in German] I’ll play the piano again.
On the Polish radio.

1250
02:15:09.874 --> 02:15:11.499
[in German] Tell me your name.

1251
02:15:11.874 --> 02:15:13.749
[in German] I’ll listen out for you.

1252
02:15:14.707 --> 02:15:15.957
Szpilman.

1253
02:15:17.207 --> 02:15:18.207
Szpilman.

1254
02:15:19.082 --> 02:15:20.291
[officer chuckles]

1255
02:15:21.332 --> 02:15:23.374
[in German] Good name for a pianist.

1256
02:15:27.249 --> 02:15:29.332
[door opens, closes]

1257
02:15:35.624 --> 02:15:36.832
[rapid gunfire nearby]

1258
02:15:37.666 --> 02:15:40.166
[Polish national anthem playing nearby]

1259
02:15:44.499 --> 02:15:46.791
[Polish national anthem blares
from cars loudspeaker]

1260
02:16:14.082 --> 02:16:16.041
[dog barks nearby]

1261
02:16:46.166 --> 02:16:49.124
[woman shouts] German! German!

1262
02:16:52.499 --> 02:16:53.374
[gunshot]

1263
02:16:54.082 --> 02:16:55.082
[Wladek groans]

1264
02:16:55.707 --> 02:16:56.666
[gunshot]

1265
02:17:03.957 --> 02:17:05.749
[Wladek groans]
[rapid gunfire]

1266
02:17:06.707 --> 02:17:07.582
[Wladek groans]

1267
02:17:07.749 --> 02:17:09.457
[explosion]

1268
02:17:10.207 --> 02:17:11.707
No! No!

1269
02:17:12.166 --> 02:17:14.666
No! Don't shoot! I'm, I'm Polish!

1270
02:17:14.832 --> 02:17:16.582
-[gunshot]
-Please! I'm Polish!

1271
02:17:17.374 --> 02:17:18.541
-[gunshot]
-I'm...

1272
02:17:18.624 --> 02:17:19.957
[Polish Officer shouts]
Come out with your hands up!

1273
02:17:20.124 --> 02:17:21.041
[Wladek] Please! I beg of you!

1274
02:17:21.832 --> 02:17:26.624
Don't shoot, don't shoot, don't shoot.
I beg you, I'm a Polish, please.

1275
02:17:26.791 --> 02:17:28.499
[Polish Officer shouts] Come down!

1276
02:17:32.374 --> 02:17:36.832
Please, I'm Polish! Please... please.

1277
02:17:36.916 --> 02:17:37.999
[Polish Officer] He's Polish.

1278
02:17:41.707 --> 02:17:43.749
[Polish Officer #2] Yes, he's Polish.

1279
02:17:45.249 --> 02:17:46.791
[Polish Officer #2] Why the fucking coat?

1280
02:17:48.749 --> 02:17:50.416
I'm cold.

1281
02:17:53.582 --> 02:17:55.124
[dog barks nearby]

1282
02:18:07.041 --> 02:18:09.207
[soldiers speaking German indistinctly]

1283
02:18:10.207 --> 02:18:12.582
Look at them. German fuckers!

1284
02:18:13.749 --> 02:18:16.541
[Lednicki] Murderers! Murderers!

1285
02:18:17.166 --> 02:18:20.291
-Dirty bastards!
-[Lednicki] Assassins!

1286
02:18:20.374 --> 02:18:23.374
-[Polish man] Bastards!
-[Lednicki] Look at you now!

1287
02:18:24.082 --> 02:18:27.916
You took everything I had.
Me, a musician.

1288
02:18:27.999 --> 02:18:31.332
You took my violin! You took my soul!

1289
02:18:36.207 --> 02:18:37.624
Musician?

1290
02:18:39.082 --> 02:18:40.166
[in German] Musician?

1291
02:18:41.249 --> 02:18:42.124
[in German] Yes.

1292
02:18:42.207 --> 02:18:46.916
[in German]
Do you know a pianist named Szpilman?

1293
02:18:46.999 --> 02:18:48.374
[in German] Polish radio?

1294
02:18:48.541 --> 02:18:50.291
[in German] Of course I know him.

1295
02:18:50.457 --> 02:18:54.374
[in German] I helped him when
he was in hiding. Tell him I'm here.

1296
02:18:54.457 --> 02:18:58.166
-[Russian Guard speaking Russian]
-[Captain in German] Ask him to help me.

1297
02:19:00.249 --> 02:19:01.957
[Russian Guard speaking Russian]

1298
02:19:02.041 --> 02:19:03.207
[in German] What's your name?

1299
02:19:03.374 --> 02:19:04.916
[German Officer] Hosenfeld.

1300
02:19:05.082 --> 02:19:08.416
-[in German] What?
-[Russian Guard speaking Russian]

1301
02:19:12.332 --> 02:19:14.624
[classical piano playing]

1302
02:20:48.582 --> 02:20:50.457
[Lednicki] It was here, I'm certain of it.

1303
02:20:51.416 --> 02:20:52.957
[dog barks in the distance]

1304
02:20:53.041 --> 02:20:54.666
[Wladek] Well, it's not here now.

1305
02:20:55.416 --> 02:20:58.957
[Lednicki] I shouted, abuse at them.
I'm not proud of it but that's what I did.

1306
02:20:59.832 --> 02:21:01.582
[Lednicki] And I'm certain
I stood where you are now.

1307
02:21:01.957 --> 02:21:05.249
[Lednicki] There was barbed wire,
and this German came up to me.

1308
02:21:07.166 --> 02:21:09.916
-[Wladek] You didn't catch his name?
-No.

1309
02:21:12.874 --> 02:21:15.041
I’ll ask at the factory.
They may know something.

1310
02:21:20.749 --> 02:21:22.582
[dog barks in the distance]
[birds chirp]

1311
02:21:37.957 --> 02:21:40.916
["Chopin's Piano Concerto No 1 " playing]

1312
02:28:47.416 --> 02:28:50.916
[round of applause]

